var book = {
	"name": "Luke",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Many have undertaken to draw up an account of the things that have been fulfilled among us,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>just as they were handed down to us by those who from the first<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24896B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24896B\"></sup> were eyewitnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24896C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24896C\"></sup> and servants of the word.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24896D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24896D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>With this in mind, since I myself have carefully investigated everything from the beginning, I too decided to write an orderly account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24897E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24897E\"></sup> for you, most excellent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24897F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24897F\"></sup> Theophilus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24897G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24897G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>so that you may know the certainty of the things you have been taught.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24898H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24898H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the time of Herod king of Judea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24899I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24899I\"></sup> there was a priest named Zechariah, who belonged to the priestly division of Abijah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24899J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24899J\"></sup> his wife Elizabeth was also a descendant of Aaron.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Both of them were righteous in the sight of God, observing all the Lord’s commands and decrees blamelessly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24900K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24900K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But they were childless because Elizabeth was not able to conceive, and they were both very old.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Once when Zechariah’s division was on duty and he was serving as priest before God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24902L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24902L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>he was chosen by lot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24903M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24903M\"></sup> according to the custom of the priesthood, to go into the temple of the Lord and burn incense.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24903N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24903N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And when the time for the burning of incense came, all the assembled worshipers were praying outside.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24904O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24904O\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24905P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24905P\"></sup> of the Lord appeared to him, standing at the right side of the altar of incense.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24905Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24905Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Zechariah saw him, he was startled and was gripped with fear.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24906R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24906R\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the angel said to him: “Do not be afraid,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24907S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24907S\"></sup> Zechariah; your prayer has been heard. Your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, and you are to call him John.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24907T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24907T\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He will be a joy and delight to you, and many will rejoice because of his birth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24908U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24908U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>for he will be great in the sight of the Lord. He is never to take wine or other fermented drink,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24909V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24909V\"></sup> and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24909W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24909W\"></sup> even before he is born.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24909X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24909X\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He will bring back many of the people of Israel to the Lord their God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he will go on before the Lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24911Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24911Y\"></sup> in the spirit and power of Elijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24911Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24911Z\"></sup> to turn the hearts of the parents to their children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24911AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24911AA\"></sup> and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous—to make ready a people prepared for the Lord.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24911AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24911AB\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Zechariah asked the angel, “How can I be sure of this?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24912AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24912AC\"></sup> I am an old man and my wife is well along in years.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24912AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24912AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The angel said to him, “I am Gabriel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24913AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24913AE\"></sup> I stand in the presence of God, and I have been sent to speak to you and to tell you this good news.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And now you will be silent and not able to speak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24914AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24914AF\"></sup> until the day this happens, because you did not believe my words, which will come true at their appointed time.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Meanwhile, the people were waiting for Zechariah and wondering why he stayed so long in the temple.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When he came out, he could not speak to them. They realized he had seen a vision in the temple, for he kept making signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24916AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24916AG\"></sup> to them but remained unable to speak.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When his time of service was completed, he returned home.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After this his wife Elizabeth became pregnant and for five months remained in seclusion.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“The Lord has done this for me,” she said. “In these days he has shown his favor and taken away my disgrace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24919AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24919AH\"></sup> among the people.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>In the sixth month of Elizabeth’s pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24920AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24920AI\"></sup> to Nazareth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24920AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24920AJ\"></sup> a town in Galilee,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>to a virgin pledged to be married to a man named Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24921AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24921AK\"></sup> a descendant of David. The virgin’s name was Mary.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The angel went to her and said, “Greetings, you who are highly favored! The Lord is with you.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Mary was greatly troubled at his words and wondered what kind of greeting this might be.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But the angel said to her, “Do not be afraid,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24924AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24924AL\"></sup> Mary; you have found favor with God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24924AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24924AM\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>You will conceive and give birth to a son, and you are to call him Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24925AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24925AN\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He will be great and will be called the Son of the Most High.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24926AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24926AO\"></sup> The Lord God will give him the throne of his father David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24926AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24926AP\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and he will reign over Jacob’s descendants forever; his kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24927AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24927AQ\"></sup> will never end.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24927AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24927AR\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“How will this be,” Mary asked the angel, “since I am a virgin?”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The angel answered, “The Holy Spirit will come on you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24929AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24929AS\"></sup> and the power of the Most High<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24929AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24929AT\"></sup> will overshadow you. So the holy one<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24929AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24929AU\"></sup> to be born will be called the Son of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24929AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24929AV\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Even Elizabeth your relative is going to have a child<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24930AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24930AW\"></sup> in her old age, and she who was said to be unable to conceive is in her sixth month.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For no word from God will ever fail.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24931AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24931AX\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“I am the Lord’s servant,” Mary answered. “May your word to me be fulfilled.” Then the angel left her.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>At that time Mary got ready and hurried to a town in the hill country of Judea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24933AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24933AY\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>where she entered Zechariah’s home and greeted Elizabeth.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>When Elizabeth heard Mary’s greeting, the baby leaped in her womb, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24935AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24935AZ\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>In a loud voice she exclaimed: “Blessed are you among women,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24936BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24936BA\"></sup> and blessed is the child you will bear!",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But why am I so favored, that the mother of my Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24937BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24937BB\"></sup> should come to me?",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>As soon as the sound of your greeting reached my ears, the baby in my womb leaped for joy.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Blessed is she who has believed that the Lord would fulfill his promises to her!”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And Mary said:“My soul glorifies the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24940BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24940BD\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>and my spirit rejoices in God my Savior,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24941BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24941BE\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>for he has been mindfulof the humble state of his servant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24942BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24942BF\"></sup>From now on all generations will call me blessed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24942BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24942BG\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>for the Mighty One has done great things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24943BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24943BH\"></sup> for me—holy is his name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24943BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24943BI\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>His mercy extends to those who fear him,from generation to generation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24944BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24944BJ\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>He has performed mighty deeds with his arm;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24945BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24945BK\"></sup>he has scattered those who are proud in their inmost thoughts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24945BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24945BL\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He has brought down rulers from their thronesbut has lifted up the humble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24946BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24946BM\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>He has filled the hungry with good things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24947BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24947BN\"></sup>but has sent the rich away empty.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>He has helped his servant Israel,remembering to be merciful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24948BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24948BO\"></sup>",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>to Abraham and his descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24949BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24949BP\"></sup> forever,just as he promised our ancestors.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Mary stayed with Elizabeth for about three months and then returned home.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>When it was time for Elizabeth to have her baby, she gave birth to a son.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Her neighbors and relatives heard that the Lord had shown her great mercy, and they shared her joy.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>On the eighth day they came to circumcise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24953BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24953BQ\"></sup> the child, and they were going to name him after his father Zechariah,",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>but his mother spoke up and said, “No! He is to be called John.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24954BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24954BR\"></sup>",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>They said to her, “There is no one among your relatives who has that name.”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Then they made signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24956BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24956BS\"></sup> to his father, to find out what he would like to name the child.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>He asked for a writing tablet, and to everyone’s astonishment he wrote, “His name is John.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24957BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24957BT\"></sup>",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>Immediately his mouth was opened and his tongue set free, and he began to speak,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24958BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24958BU\"></sup> praising God.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>All the neighbors were filled with awe, and throughout the hill country of Judea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24959BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24959BV\"></sup> people were talking about all these things.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>Everyone who heard this wondered about it, asking, “What then is this child going to be?” For the Lord’s hand was with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24960BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24960BW\"></sup>",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>His father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24961BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24961BX\"></sup> and prophesied:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24961BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24961BY\"></sup>",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>“Praise be to the Lord, the God of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24962BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24962BZ\"></sup>because he has come to his people and redeemed them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24962CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24962CA\"></sup>",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>He has raised up a horn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24963CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24963CB\"></sup> of salvation for usin the house of his servant David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24963CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24963CC\"></sup>",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>(as he said through his holy prophets of long ago),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24964CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24964CD\"></sup>",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>salvation from our enemiesand from the hand of all who hate us—",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>to show mercy to our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24966CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24966CE\"></sup>and to remember his holy covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24966CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24966CF\"></sup>",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>the oath he swore to our father Abraham:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24967CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24967CG\"></sup>",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>to rescue us from the hand of our enemies,and to enable us to serve him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24968CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24968CH\"></sup> without fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24968CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24968CI\"></sup>",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>in holiness and righteousness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24969CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24969CJ\"></sup> before him all our days.",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>And you, my child, will be called a prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24970CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24970CK\"></sup> of the Most High;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24970CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24970CL\"></sup>for you will go on before the Lord to prepare the way for him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24970CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24970CM\"></sup>",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup>to give his people the knowledge of salvationthrough the forgiveness of their sins,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24971CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24971CN\"></sup>",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>because of the tender mercy of our God,by which the rising sun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24972CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24972CO\"></sup> will come to us from heaven",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup>to shine on those living in darknessand in the shadow of death,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24973CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24973CP\"></sup>to guide our feet into the path of peace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24973CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24973CQ\"></sup>",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup>And the child grew and became strong in spirit;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24974CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24974CR\"></sup> and he lived in the wilderness until he appeared publicly to Israel."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>In those days Caesar Augustus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24975A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24975A\"></sup> issued a decree that a census should be taken of the entire Roman world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24975B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24975B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>(This was the first census that took place while Quirinius was governor of Syria.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24976C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24976C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And everyone went to their own town to register.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Joseph also went up from the town of Nazareth in Galilee to Judea, to Bethlehem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24978D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24978D\"></sup> the town of David, because he belonged to the house and line of David.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He went there to register with Mary, who was pledged to be married to him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24979E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24979E\"></sup> and was expecting a child.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>While they were there, the time came for the baby to be born,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and she gave birth to her firstborn, a son. She wrapped him in cloths and placed him in a manger, because there was no guest room available for them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And there were shepherds living out in the fields nearby, keeping watch over their flocks at night.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>An angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24983F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24983F\"></sup> of the Lord appeared to them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were terrified.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the angel said to them, “Do not be afraid.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24984G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24984G\"></sup> I bring you good news that will cause great joy for all the people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Today in the town of David a Savior<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24985H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24985H\"></sup> has been born to you; he is the Messiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24985I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24985I\"></sup> the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24985J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24985J\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>This will be a sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24986K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24986K\"></sup> to you: You will find a baby wrapped in cloths and lying in a manger.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Suddenly a great company of the heavenly host appeared with the angel, praising God and saying,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Glory to God in the highest heaven,and on earth peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24988L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24988L\"></sup> to those on whom his favor rests.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the angels had left them and gone into heaven, the shepherds said to one another, “Let’s go to Bethlehem and see this thing that has happened, which the Lord has told us about.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they hurried off and found Mary and Joseph, and the baby, who was lying in the manger.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24990M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24990M\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When they had seen him, they spread the word concerning what had been told them about this child,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and all who heard it were amazed at what the shepherds said to them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Mary treasured up all these things and pondered them in her heart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24993N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24993N\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24994O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24994O\"></sup> for all the things they had heard and seen, which were just as they had been told.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>On the eighth day, when it was time to circumcise the child,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24995P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24995P\"></sup> he was named Jesus, the name the angel had given him before he was conceived.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24995Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24995Q\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When the time came for the purification rites required by the Law of Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24996R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24996R\"></sup> Joseph and Mary took him to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>(as it is written in the Law of the Lord, “Every firstborn male is to be consecrated to the Lord”),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24997S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24997S\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and to offer a sacrifice in keeping with what is said in the Law of the Lord: “a pair of doves or two young pigeons.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24998T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24998T\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now there was a man in Jerusalem called Simeon, who was righteous and devout.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24999U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24999U\"></sup> He was waiting for the consolation of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24999V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24999V\"></sup> and the Holy Spirit was on him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he would not die before he had seen the Lord’s Messiah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Moved by the Spirit, he went into the temple courts. When the parents brought in the child Jesus to do for him what the custom of the Law required,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25001W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25001W\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Simeon took him in his arms and praised God, saying:",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Sovereign Lord, as you have promised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25003X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25003X\"></sup>you may now dismiss your servant in peace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25003Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25003Y\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For my eyes have seen your salvation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25004Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25004Z\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>which you have prepared in the sight of all nations:",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>a light for revelation to the Gentiles,and the glory of your people Israel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25006AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25006AA\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The child’s father and mother marveled at what was said about him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Simeon blessed them and said to Mary, his mother:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25008AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25008AB\"></sup> “This child is destined to cause the falling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25008AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25008AC\"></sup> and rising of many in Israel, and to be a sign that will be spoken against,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>so that the thoughts of many hearts will be revealed. And a sword will pierce your own soul too.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>There was also a prophet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25010AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25010AD\"></sup> Anna, the daughter of Penuel, of the tribe of Asher. She was very old; she had lived with her husband seven years after her marriage,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and then was a widow until she was eighty-four.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25011AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25011AE\"></sup> She never left the temple but worshiped night and day, fasting and praying.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25011AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25011AF\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Coming up to them at that very moment, she gave thanks to God and spoke about the child to all who were looking forward to the redemption of Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25012AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25012AG\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When Joseph and Mary had done everything required by the Law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee to their own town of Nazareth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25013AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25013AH\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And the child grew and became strong; he was filled with wisdom, and the grace of God was on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25014AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25014AI\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Every year Jesus’ parents went to Jerusalem for the Festival of the Passover.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25015AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25015AJ\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>When he was twelve years old, they went up to the festival, according to the custom.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>After the festival was over, while his parents were returning home, the boy Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem, but they were unaware of it.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Thinking he was in their company, they traveled on for a day. Then they began looking for him among their relatives and friends.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When they did not find him, they went back to Jerusalem to look for him.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>After three days they found him in the temple courts, sitting among the teachers, listening to them and asking them questions.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Everyone who heard him was amazed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25021AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25021AK\"></sup> at his understanding and his answers.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>When his parents saw him, they were astonished. His mother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25022AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25022AL\"></sup> said to him, “Son, why have you treated us like this? Your father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25022AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25022AM\"></sup> and I have been anxiously searching for you.”",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“Why were you searching for me?”</span> he asked. <span class=\"woj\">“Didn’t you know I had to be in my Father’s house?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25023AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25023AN\"></sup></span>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But they did not understand what he was saying to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25024AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25024AO\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then he went down to Nazareth with them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25025AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25025AP\"></sup> and was obedient to them. But his mother treasured all these things in her heart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25025AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25025AQ\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And Jesus grew in wisdom and stature, and in favor with God and man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25026AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25026AR\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>In the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar—when Pontius Pilate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25027C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25027C\"></sup> was governor of Judea, Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25027D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25027D\"></sup> tetrarch of Galilee, his brother Philip tetrarch of Iturea and Traconitis, and Lysanias tetrarch of Abilene—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>during the high-priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25028E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25028E\"></sup> the word of God came to John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25028F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25028F\"></sup> son of Zechariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25028G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25028G\"></sup> in the wilderness.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He went into all the country around the Jordan, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25029H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25029H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet:“A voice of one calling in the wilderness,‘Prepare the way for the Lord,make straight paths for him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Every valley shall be filled in,every mountain and hill made low.The crooked roads shall become straight,the rough ways smooth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And all people will see God’s salvation.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25032I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25032I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>John said to the crowds coming out to be baptized by him, “You brood of vipers!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25033J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25033J\"></sup> Who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25033K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25033K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Produce fruit in keeping with repentance. And do not begin to say to yourselves, ‘We have Abraham as our father.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25034L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25034L\"></sup> For I tell you that out of these stones God can raise up children for Abraham.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The ax is already at the root of the trees, and every tree that does not produce good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25035M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25035M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“What should we do then?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25036N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25036N\"></sup> the crowd asked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>John answered, “Anyone who has two shirts should share with the one who has none, and anyone who has food should do the same.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25037O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25037O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Even tax collectors came to be baptized.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25038P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25038P\"></sup> “Teacher,” they asked, “what should we do?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Don’t collect any more than you are required to,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25039Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25039Q\"></sup> he told them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then some soldiers asked him, “And what should we do?”He replied, “Don’t extort money and don’t accuse people falsely<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25040R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25040R\"></sup>—be content with your pay.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The people were waiting expectantly and were all wondering in their hearts if John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25041S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25041S\"></sup> might possibly be the Messiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25041T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25041T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>John answered them all, “I baptize you with water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25042U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25042U\"></sup> But one who is more powerful than I will come, the straps of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25042V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25042V\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>His winnowing fork<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25043W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25043W\"></sup> is in his hand to clear his threshing floor and to gather the wheat into his barn, but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25043X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And with many other words John exhorted the people and proclaimed the good news to them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when John rebuked Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25045Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25045Y\"></sup> the tetrarch because of his marriage to Herodias, his brother’s wife, and all the other evil things he had done,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Herod added this to them all: He locked John up in prison.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25046Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25046Z\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When all the people were being baptized, Jesus was baptized too. And as he was praying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25047AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25047AC\"></sup> heaven was opened",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and the Holy Spirit descended on him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25048AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25048AD\"></sup> in bodily form like a dove. And a voice came from heaven: “You are my Son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25048AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25048AE\"></sup> whom I love; with you I am well pleased.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25048AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25048AF\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now Jesus himself was about thirty years old when he began his ministry.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25049AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25049AG\"></sup> He was the son, so it was thought, of Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25049AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25049AH\"></sup>the son of Heli,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the son of Matthat,the son of Levi, the son of Melki,the son of Jannai, the son of Joseph,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the son of Mattathias, the son of Amos,the son of Nahum, the son of Esli,the son of Naggai,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>the son of Maath,the son of Mattathias, the son of Semein,the son of Josek, the son of Joda,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>the son of Joanan, the son of Rhesa,the son of Zerubbabel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25053AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25053AI\"></sup> the son of Shealtiel,the son of Neri,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>the son of Melki,the son of Addi, the son of Cosam,the son of Elmadam, the son of Er,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>the son of Joshua, the son of Eliezer,the son of Jorim, the son of Matthat,the son of Levi,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the son of Simeon,the son of Judah, the son of Joseph,the son of Jonam, the son of Eliakim,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the son of Melea, the son of Menna,the son of Mattatha, the son of Nathan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25057AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25057AJ\"></sup>the son of David,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>the son of Jesse,the son of Obed, the son of Boaz,the son of Salmon, the son of Nahshon,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>the son of Amminadab, the son of Ram,the son of Hezron, the son of Perez,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25059AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25059AK\"></sup>the son of Judah,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the son of Jacob,the son of Isaac, the son of Abraham,the son of Terah, the son of Nahor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25060AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25060AL\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the son of Serug, the son of Reu,the son of Peleg, the son of Eber,the son of Shelah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the son of Cainan,the son of Arphaxad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25062AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25062AM\"></sup> the son of Shem,the son of Noah, the son of Lamech,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25062AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25062AN\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the son of Methuselah, the son of Enoch,the son of Jared, the son of Mahalalel,the son of Kenan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25063AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25063AO\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>the son of Enosh,the son of Seth, the son of Adam,the son of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25064AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25064AP\"></sup>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25065B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25065B\"></sup> left the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25065C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25065C\"></sup> and was led by the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25065D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25065D\"></sup> into the wilderness,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>where for forty days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25066E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25066E\"></sup> he was tempted by the devil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25066F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25066F\"></sup> He ate nothing during those days, and at the end of them he was hungry.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The devil said to him, “If you are the Son of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25067G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25067G\"></sup> tell this stone to become bread.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“It is written: ‘Man shall not live on bread alone.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25068H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25068H\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The devil led him up to a high place and showed him in an instant all the kingdoms of the world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25069I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25069I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he said to him, “I will give you all their authority and splendor; it has been given to me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25070J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25070J\"></sup> and I can give it to anyone I want to.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If you worship me, it will all be yours.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“It is written: ‘Worship the Lord your God and serve him only.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25072K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25072K\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The devil led him to Jerusalem and had him stand on the highest point of the temple. “If you are the Son of God,” he said, “throw yourself down from here.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For it is written:“‘He will command his angels concerning youto guard you carefully;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>they will lift you up in their hands,so that you will not strike your foot against a stone.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25075L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25075L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“It is said: ‘Do not put the Lord your God to the test.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25076M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25076M\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When the devil had finished all this tempting,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25077N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25077N\"></sup> he left him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25077O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25077O\"></sup> until an opportune time.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jesus returned to Galilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25078P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25078P\"></sup> in the power of the Spirit, and news about him spread through the whole countryside.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25078Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25078Q\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He was teaching in their synagogues,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25079R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25079R\"></sup> and everyone praised him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He went to Nazareth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25080S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25080S\"></sup> where he had been brought up, and on the Sabbath day he went into the synagogue,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25080T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25080T\"></sup> as was his custom. He stood up to read,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25080U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25080U\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the scroll of the prophet Isaiah was handed to him. Unrolling it, he found the place where it is written:",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“The Spirit of the Lord is on me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25082V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25082V\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">because he has anointed me</span><span class=\"woj\">to proclaim good news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25082W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25082W\"></sup> to the poor.</span><span class=\"woj\">He has sent me to proclaim freedom for the prisoners</span><span class=\"woj\">and recovery of sight for the blind,</span><span class=\"woj\">to set the oppressed free,</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>to proclaim the year of the Lord’s favor.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25083X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25083X\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he rolled up the scroll, gave it back to the attendant and sat down.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25084Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25084Y\"></sup> The eyes of everyone in the synagogue were fastened on him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He began by saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Today this scripture is fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25085Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25085Z\"></sup> in your hearing.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>All spoke well of him and were amazed at the gracious words that came from his lips. “Isn’t this Joseph’s son?” they asked.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25086AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25086AA\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Surely you will quote this proverb to me: ‘Physician, heal yourself!’ And you will tell me, ‘Do here in your hometown<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25087AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25087AB\"></sup> what we have heard that you did in Capernaum.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25087AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25087AC\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Truly I tell you,”</span> he continued, <span class=\"woj\">“no prophet is accepted in his hometown.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25088AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25088AD\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I assure you that there were many widows in Israel in Elijah’s time, when the sky was shut for three and a half years and there was a severe famine throughout the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25089AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25089AE\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Yet Elijah was not sent to any of them, but to a widow in Zarephath in the region of Sidon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25090AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25090AF\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And there were many in Israel with leprosy in the time of Elisha the prophet, yet not one of them was cleansed—only Naaman the Syrian.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25091AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25091AG\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All the people in the synagogue were furious when they heard this.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They got up, drove him out of the town,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25093AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25093AH\"></sup> and took him to the brow of the hill on which the town was built, in order to throw him off the cliff.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But he walked right through the crowd and went on his way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25094AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25094AI\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he went down to Capernaum,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25095AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25095AK\"></sup> a town in Galilee, and on the Sabbath he taught the people.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They were amazed at his teaching,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25096AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25096AL\"></sup> because his words had authority.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25096AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25096AM\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the synagogue there was a man possessed by a demon, an impure spirit. He cried out at the top of his voice,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Go away! What do you want with us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25098AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25098AN\"></sup> Jesus of Nazareth?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25098AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25098AO\"></sup> Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25098AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25098AP\"></sup>—the Holy One of God!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25098AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25098AQ\"></sup>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“Be quiet!”</span> Jesus said sternly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25099AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25099AR\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">“Come out of him!”</span> Then the demon threw the man down before them all and came out without injuring him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>All the people were amazed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25100AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25100AS\"></sup> and said to each other, “What words these are! With authority<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25100AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25100AT\"></sup> and power he gives orders to impure spirits and they come out!”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And the news about him spread throughout the surrounding area.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25101AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25101AU\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Jesus left the synagogue and went to the home of Simon. Now Simon’s mother-in-law was suffering from a high fever, and they asked Jesus to help her.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>So he bent over her and rebuked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25103AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25103AX\"></sup> the fever, and it left her. She got up at once and began to wait on them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>At sunset, the people brought to Jesus all who had various kinds of sickness, and laying his hands on each one,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25104AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25104AY\"></sup> he healed them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25104AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25104AZ\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Moreover, demons came out of many people, shouting, “You are the Son of God!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25105BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25105BA\"></sup> But he rebuked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25105BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25105BB\"></sup> them and would not allow them to speak,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25105BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25105BC\"></sup> because they knew he was the Messiah.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>At daybreak, Jesus went out to a solitary place. The people were looking for him and when they came to where he was, they tried to keep him from leaving them.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But he said, <span class=\"woj\">“I must proclaim the good news of the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25107BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25107BD\"></sup> to the other towns also, because that is why I was sent.”</span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>And he kept on preaching in the synagogues of Judea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25108BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25108BE\"></sup>"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>One day as Jesus was standing by the Lake of Gennesaret, the people were crowding around him and listening to the word of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25109B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25109B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He saw at the water’s edge two boats, left there by the fishermen, who were washing their nets.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He got into one of the boats, the one belonging to Simon, and asked him to put out a little from shore. Then he sat down and taught the people from the boat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25111C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25111C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When he had finished speaking, he said to Simon, <span class=\"woj\">“Put out into deep water, and let down the nets for a catch.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25112D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25112D\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Simon answered, “Master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25113E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25113E\"></sup> we’ve worked hard all night and haven’t caught anything.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25113F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25113F\"></sup> But because you say so, I will let down the nets.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they had done so, they caught such a large number of fish that their nets began to break.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25114G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25114G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they signaled their partners in the other boat to come and help them, and they came and filled both boats so full that they began to sink.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Simon Peter saw this, he fell at Jesus’ knees and said, “Go away from me, Lord; I am a sinful man!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25116H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25116H\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For he and all his companions were astonished at the catch of fish they had taken,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and so were James and John, the sons of Zebedee, Simon’s partners.Then Jesus said to Simon, <span class=\"woj\">“Don’t be afraid;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25118I\"></sup> from now on you will fish for people.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So they pulled their boats up on shore, left everything and followed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25119J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25119J\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>While Jesus was in one of the towns, a man came along who was covered with leprosy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25120L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25120L\"></sup> When he saw Jesus, he fell with his face to the ground and begged him, “Lord, if you are willing, you can make me clean.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesus reached out his hand and touched the man. <span class=\"woj\">“I am willing,”</span> he said. <span class=\"woj\">“Be clean!”</span> And immediately the leprosy left him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Jesus ordered him, <span class=\"woj\">“Don’t tell anyone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25122M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25122M\"></sup> but go, show yourself to the priest and offer the sacrifices that Moses commanded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25122N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25122N\"></sup> for your cleansing, as a testimony to them.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Yet the news about him spread all the more,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25123O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25123O\"></sup> so that crowds of people came to hear him and to be healed of their sicknesses.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But Jesus often withdrew to lonely places and prayed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25124P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25124P\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>One day Jesus was teaching, and Pharisees and teachers of the law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25125R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25125R\"></sup> were sitting there. They had come from every village of Galilee and from Judea and Jerusalem. And the power of the Lord was with Jesus to heal the sick.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25125S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25125S\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Some men came carrying a paralyzed man on a mat and tried to take him into the house to lay him before Jesus.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When they could not find a way to do this because of the crowd, they went up on the roof and lowered him on his mat through the tiles into the middle of the crowd, right in front of Jesus.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Jesus saw their faith, he said, <span class=\"woj\">“Friend, your sins are forgiven.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25128T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25128T\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The Pharisees and the teachers of the law began thinking to themselves, “Who is this fellow who speaks blasphemy? Who can forgive sins but God alone?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25129U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25129U\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Jesus knew what they were thinking and asked, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you thinking these things in your hearts?</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Which is easier: to say, ‘Your sins are forgiven,’ or to say, ‘Get up and walk’?</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But I want you to know that the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25132V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25132V\"></sup> has authority on earth to forgive sins.”</span> So he said to the paralyzed man, <span class=\"woj\">“I tell you, get up, take your mat and go home.”</span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Immediately he stood up in front of them, took what he had been lying on and went home praising God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Everyone was amazed and gave praise to God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25134W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25134W\"></sup> They were filled with awe and said, “We have seen remarkable things today.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>After this, Jesus went out and saw a tax collector by the name of Levi sitting at his tax booth. <span class=\"woj\">“Follow me,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25135Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25135Y\"></sup></span> Jesus said to him,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and Levi got up, left everything and followed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25136Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25136Z\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Levi held a great banquet for Jesus at his house, and a large crowd of tax collectors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25137AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25137AA\"></sup> and others were eating with them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But the Pharisees and the teachers of the law who belonged to their sect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25138AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25138AB\"></sup> complained to his disciples, “Why do you eat and drink with tax collectors and sinners?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25138AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25138AC\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jesus answered them, <span class=\"woj\">“It is not the healthy who need a doctor, but the sick.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>I have not come to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25140AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25140AD\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They said to him, “John’s disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25141AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25141AF\"></sup> often fast and pray, and so do the disciples of the Pharisees, but yours go on eating and drinking.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Can you make the friends of the bridegroom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25142AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25142AG\"></sup> fast while he is with them?</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But the time will come when the bridegroom will be taken from them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25143AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25143AH\"></sup> in those days they will fast.”</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He told them this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“No one tears a piece out of a new garment to patch an old one. Otherwise, they will have torn the new garment, and the patch from the new will not match the old.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And no one pours new wine into old wineskins. Otherwise, the new wine will burst the skins; the wine will run out and the wineskins will be ruined.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>No, new wine must be poured into new wineskins.</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And no one after drinking old wine wants the new, for they say, ‘The old is better.’”</span>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>One Sabbath Jesus was going through the grainfields, and his disciples began to pick some heads of grain, rub them in their hands and eat the kernels.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25148B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25148B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Some of the Pharisees asked, “Why are you doing what is unlawful on the Sabbath?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25149C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25149C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jesus answered them, <span class=\"woj\">“Have you never read what David did when he and his companions were hungry?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25150D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25150D\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He entered the house of God, and taking the consecrated bread, he ate what is lawful only for priests to eat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25151E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25151E\"></sup> And he also gave some to his companions.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“The Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25152F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25152F\"></sup> is Lord of the Sabbath.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>On another Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25153G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25153G\"></sup> he went into the synagogue and was teaching, and a man was there whose right hand was shriveled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Pharisees and the teachers of the law were looking for a reason to accuse Jesus, so they watched him closely<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25154H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25154H\"></sup> to see if he would heal on the Sabbath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25154I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25154I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Jesus knew what they were thinking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25155J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25155J\"></sup> and said to the man with the shriveled hand, <span class=\"woj\">“Get up and stand in front of everyone.”</span> So he got up and stood there.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I ask you, which is lawful on the Sabbath: to do good or to do evil, to save life or to destroy it?”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He looked around at them all, and then said to the man, <span class=\"woj\">“Stretch out your hand.”</span> He did so, and his hand was completely restored.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the Pharisees and the teachers of the law were furious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25158K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25158K\"></sup> and began to discuss with one another what they might do to Jesus.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>One of those days Jesus went out to a mountainside to pray, and spent the night praying to God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25159M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25159M\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When morning came, he called his disciples to him and chose twelve of them, whom he also designated apostles:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25160N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25160N\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Simon (whom he named Peter), his brother Andrew, James, John, Philip, Bartholomew,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Matthew,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25162O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25162O\"></sup> Thomas, James son of Alphaeus, Simon who was called the Zealot,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Judas son of James, and Judas Iscariot, who became a traitor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He went down with them and stood on a level place. A large crowd of his disciples was there and a great number of people from all over Judea, from Jerusalem, and from the coastal region around Tyre and Sidon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25164Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25164Q\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>who had come to hear him and to be healed of their diseases. Those troubled by impure spirits were cured,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and the people all tried to touch him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25166R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25166R\"></sup> because power was coming from him and healing them all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25166S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25166S\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Looking at his disciples, he said:<span class=\"woj\">“Blessed are you who are poor,</span><span class=\"woj\">for yours is the kingdom of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25167T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25167T\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Blessed are you who hunger now,</span><span class=\"woj\">for you will be satisfied.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25168U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25168U\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">Blessed are you who weep now,</span><span class=\"woj\">for you will laugh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25168V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25168V\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Blessed are you when people hate you,</span><span class=\"woj\">when they exclude you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25169W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25169W\"></sup> and insult you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25169X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25169X\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">and reject your name as evil,</span><span class=\"woj\">because of the Son of Man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25169Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25169Y\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Rejoice in that day and leap for joy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25170Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25170Z\"></sup> because great is your reward in heaven. For that is how their ancestors treated the prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25170AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25170AA\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“But woe to you who are rich,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25171AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25171AB\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">for you have already received your comfort.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25171AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25171AC\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Woe to you who are well fed now,</span><span class=\"woj\">for you will go hungry.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25172AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25172AD\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">Woe to you who laugh now,</span><span class=\"woj\">for you will mourn and weep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25172AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25172AE\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Woe to you when everyone speaks well of you,</span><span class=\"woj\">for that is how their ancestors treated the false prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25173AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25173AF\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But to you who are listening I say: Love your enemies, do good to those who hate you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25174AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25174AH\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>bless those who curse you, pray for those who mistreat you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25175AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25175AI\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If someone slaps you on one cheek, turn to them the other also. If someone takes your coat, do not withhold your shirt from them.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Give to everyone who asks you, and if anyone takes what belongs to you, do not demand it back.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25177AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25177AJ\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Do to others as you would have them do to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25178AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25178AK\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“If you love those who love you, what credit is that to you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25179AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25179AL\"></sup> Even sinners love those who love them.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And if you do good to those who are good to you, what credit is that to you? Even sinners do that.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And if you lend to those from whom you expect repayment, what credit is that to you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25181AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25181AM\"></sup> Even sinners lend to sinners, expecting to be repaid in full.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But love your enemies, do good to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25182AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25182AN\"></sup> and lend to them without expecting to get anything back. Then your reward will be great, and you will be children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25182AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25182AO\"></sup> of the Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25182AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25182AP\"></sup> because he is kind to the ungrateful and wicked.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Be merciful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25183AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25183AQ\"></sup> just as your Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25183AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25183AR\"></sup> is merciful.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“Do not judge, and you will not be judged.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25184AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25184AT\"></sup> Do not condemn, and you will not be condemned. Forgive, and you will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25184AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25184AU\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Give, and it will be given to you. A good measure, pressed down, shaken together and running over, will be poured into your lap.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25185AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25185AV\"></sup> For with the measure you use, it will be measured to you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25185AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25185AW\"></sup></span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>He also told them this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“Can the blind lead the blind? Will they not both fall into a pit?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25186AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25186AX\"></sup></span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The student is not above the teacher, but everyone who is fully trained will be like their teacher.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25187AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25187AY\"></sup></span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Why do you look at the speck of sawdust in your brother’s eye and pay no attention to the plank in your own eye?</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>How can you say to your brother, ‘Brother, let me take the speck out of your eye,’ when you yourself fail to see the plank in your own eye? You hypocrite, first take the plank out of your eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the speck from your brother’s eye.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“No good tree bears bad fruit, nor does a bad tree bear good fruit.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Each tree is recognized by its own fruit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25191BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25191BA\"></sup> People do not pick figs from thornbushes, or grapes from briers.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>A good man brings good things out of the good stored up in his heart, and an evil man brings evil things out of the evil stored up in his heart. For the mouth speaks what the heart is full of.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25192BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25192BB\"></sup></span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Why do you call me, ‘Lord, Lord,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25193BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25193BD\"></sup> and do not do what I say?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25193BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25193BE\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>As for everyone who comes to me and hears my words and puts them into practice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25194BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25194BF\"></sup> I will show you what they are like.</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>They are like a man building a house, who dug down deep and laid the foundation on rock. When a flood came, the torrent struck that house but could not shake it, because it was well built.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But the one who hears my words and does not put them into practice is like a man who built a house on the ground without a foundation. The moment the torrent struck that house, it collapsed and its destruction was complete.”</span>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>When Jesus had finished saying all this<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25197B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25197B\"></sup> to the people who were listening, he entered Capernaum.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There a centurion’s servant, whom his master valued highly, was sick and about to die.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The centurion heard of Jesus and sent some elders of the Jews to him, asking him to come and heal his servant.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When they came to Jesus, they pleaded earnestly with him, “This man deserves to have you do this,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>because he loves our nation and has built our synagogue.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Jesus went with them.He was not far from the house when the centurion sent friends to say to him: “Lord, don’t trouble yourself, for I do not deserve to have you come under my roof.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>That is why I did not even consider myself worthy to come to you. But say the word, and my servant will be healed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25203C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25203C\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For I myself am a man under authority, with soldiers under me. I tell this one, ‘Go,’ and he goes; and that one, ‘Come,’ and he comes. I say to my servant, ‘Do this,’ and he does it.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Jesus heard this, he was amazed at him, and turning to the crowd following him, he said, <span class=\"woj\">“I tell you, I have not found such great faith even in Israel.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the men who had been sent returned to the house and found the servant well.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Soon afterward, Jesus went to a town called Nain, and his disciples and a large crowd went along with him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As he approached the town gate, a dead person was being carried out—the only son of his mother, and she was a widow. And a large crowd from the town was with her.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25209E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25209E\"></sup> saw her, his heart went out to her and he said, <span class=\"woj\">“Don’t cry.”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he went up and touched the bier they were carrying him on, and the bearers stood still. He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Young man, I say to you, get up!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25210F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25210F\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The dead man sat up and began to talk, and Jesus gave him back to his mother.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They were all filled with awe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25212G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25212G\"></sup> and praised God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25212H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25212H\"></sup> “A great prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25212I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25212I\"></sup> has appeared among us,” they said. “God has come to help his people.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25212J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25212J\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>This news about Jesus spread throughout Judea and the surrounding country.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25213K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25213K\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>John’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25214M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25214M\"></sup> disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25214N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25214N\"></sup> told him about all these things. Calling two of them,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>he sent them to the Lord to ask, “Are you the one who is to come, or should we expect someone else?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When the men came to Jesus, they said, “John the Baptist sent us to you to ask, ‘Are you the one who is to come, or should we expect someone else?’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>At that very time Jesus cured many who had diseases, sicknesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25217O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25217O\"></sup> and evil spirits, and gave sight to many who were blind.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So he replied to the messengers, <span class=\"woj\">“Go back and report to John what you have seen and heard: The blind receive sight, the lame walk, those who have leprosy are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, and the good news is proclaimed to the poor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25218P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25218P\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Blessed is anyone who does not stumble on account of me.”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After John’s messengers left, Jesus began to speak to the crowd about John: <span class=\"woj\">“What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed swayed by the wind?</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If not, what did you go out to see? A man dressed in fine clothes? No, those who wear expensive clothes and indulge in luxury are in palaces.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But what did you go out to see? A prophet?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25222Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25222Q\"></sup> Yes, I tell you, and more than a prophet.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>This is the one about whom it is written:</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘I will send my messenger ahead of you,</span><span class=\"woj\">who will prepare your way before you.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25223R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25223R\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I tell you, among those born of women there is no one greater than John; yet the one who is least in the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25224S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25224S\"></sup> is greater than he.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>(All the people, even the tax collectors, when they heard Jesus’ words, acknowledged that God’s way was right, because they had been baptized by John.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25225T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25225T\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But the Pharisees and the experts in the law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25226U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25226U\"></sup> rejected God’s purpose for themselves, because they had not been baptized by John.)",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jesus went on to say, <span class=\"woj\">“To what, then, can I compare the people of this generation? What are they like?</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They are like children sitting in the marketplace and calling out to each other:</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘We played the pipe for you,</span><span class=\"woj\">and you did not dance;</span><span class=\"woj\">we sang a dirge,</span><span class=\"woj\">and you did not cry.’</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>For John the Baptist came neither eating bread nor drinking wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25229V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25229V\"></sup> and you say, ‘He has a demon.’</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and you say, ‘Here is a glutton and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25230W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25230W\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But wisdom is proved right by all her children.”</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When one of the Pharisees invited Jesus to have dinner with him, he went to the Pharisee’s house and reclined at the table.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>A woman in that town who lived a sinful life learned that Jesus was eating at the Pharisee’s house, so she came there with an alabaster jar of perfume.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>As she stood behind him at his feet weeping, she began to wet his feet with her tears. Then she wiped them with her hair, kissed them and poured perfume on them.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When the Pharisee who had invited him saw this, he said to himself, “If this man were a prophet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25235Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25235Z\"></sup> he would know who is touching him and what kind of woman she is—that she is a sinner.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Jesus answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“Simon, I have something to tell you.”</span>“Tell me, teacher,” he said.",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Two people owed money to a certain moneylender. One owed him five hundred denarii, and the other fifty.</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Neither of them had the money to pay him back, so he forgave the debts of both. Now which of them will love him more?”</span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Simon replied, “I suppose the one who had the bigger debt forgiven.”<span class=\"woj\">“You have judged correctly,”</span> Jesus said.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Then he turned toward the woman and said to Simon, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you see this woman? I came into your house. You did not give me any water for my feet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25240AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25240AA\"></sup> but she wet my feet with her tears and wiped them with her hair.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>You did not give me a kiss,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25241AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25241AB\"></sup> but this woman, from the time I entered, has not stopped kissing my feet.</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>You did not put oil on my head,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25242AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25242AC\"></sup> but she has poured perfume on my feet.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Therefore, I tell you, her many sins have been forgiven—as her great love has shown. But whoever has been forgiven little loves little.”</span>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then Jesus said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Your sins are forgiven.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25244AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25244AD\"></sup></span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>The other guests began to say among themselves, “Who is this who even forgives sins?”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Jesus said to the woman, <span class=\"woj\">“Your faith has saved you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25246AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25246AE\"></sup> go in peace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25246AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25246AF\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>After this, Jesus traveled about from one town and village to another, proclaiming the good news of the kingdom of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25247B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25247B\"></sup> The Twelve were with him,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and also some women who had been cured of evil spirits and diseases: Mary (called Magdalene)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25248C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25248C\"></sup> from whom seven demons had come out;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Joanna the wife of Chuza, the manager of Herod’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25249D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25249D\"></sup> household; Susanna; and many others. These women were helping to support them out of their own means.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>While a large crowd was gathering and people were coming to Jesus from town after town, he told this parable:",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“A farmer went out to sow his seed. As he was scattering the seed, some fell along the path; it was trampled on, and the birds ate it up.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Some fell on rocky ground, and when it came up, the plants withered because they had no moisture.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Other seed fell among thorns, which grew up with it and choked the plants.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Still other seed fell on good soil. It came up and yielded a crop, a hundred times more than was sown.”</span>When he said this, he called out, <span class=\"woj\">“Whoever has ears to hear, let them hear.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25254E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25254E\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>His disciples asked him what this parable meant.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, <span class=\"woj\">“The knowledge of the secrets of the kingdom of God has been given to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25256F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25256F\"></sup> but to others I speak in parables, so that,</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘though seeing, they may not see;</span><span class=\"woj\">though hearing, they may not understand.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25256G\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“This is the meaning of the parable: The seed is the word of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25257H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25257H\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Those along the path are the ones who hear, and then the devil comes and takes away the word from their hearts, so that they may not believe and be saved.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Those on the rocky ground are the ones who receive the word with joy when they hear it, but they have no root. They believe for a while, but in the time of testing they fall away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25259I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25259I\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The seed that fell among thorns stands for those who hear, but as they go on their way they are choked by life’s worries, riches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25260J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25260J\"></sup> and pleasures, and they do not mature.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the seed on good soil stands for those with a noble and good heart, who hear the word, retain it, and by persevering produce a crop.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“No one lights a lamp and hides it in a clay jar or puts it under a bed. Instead, they put it on a stand, so that those who come in can see the light.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25262K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25262K\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For there is nothing hidden that will not be disclosed, and nothing concealed that will not be known or brought out into the open.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25263L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25263L\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Therefore consider carefully how you listen. Whoever has will be given more; whoever does not have, even what they think they have will be taken from them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25264M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25264M\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now Jesus’ mother and brothers came to see him, but they were not able to get near him because of the crowd.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Someone told him, “Your mother and brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25266O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25266O\"></sup> are standing outside, wanting to see you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“My mother and brothers are those who hear God’s word and put it into practice.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25267P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25267P\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>One day Jesus said to his disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“Let us go over to the other side of the lake.”</span> So they got into a boat and set out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As they sailed, he fell asleep. A squall came down on the lake, so that the boat was being swamped, and they were in great danger.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The disciples went and woke him, saying, “Master, Master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25270S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25270S\"></sup> we’re going to drown!”He got up and rebuked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25270T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25270T\"></sup> the wind and the raging waters; the storm subsided, and all was calm.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25270U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25270U\"></sup>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Where is your faith?”</span> he asked his disciples.In fear and amazement they asked one another, “Who is this? He commands even the winds and the water, and they obey him.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They sailed to the region of the Gerasenes, which is across the lake from Galilee.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When Jesus stepped ashore, he was met by a demon-possessed man from the town. For a long time this man had not worn clothes or lived in a house, but had lived in the tombs.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When he saw Jesus, he cried out and fell at his feet, shouting at the top of his voice, “What do you want with me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25274X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25274X\"></sup> Jesus, Son of the Most High God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25274Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25274Y\"></sup> I beg you, don’t torture me!”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For Jesus had commanded the impure spirit to come out of the man. Many times it had seized him, and though he was chained hand and foot and kept under guard, he had broken his chains and had been driven by the demon into solitary places.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Jesus asked him, <span class=\"woj\">“What is your name?”</span>“Legion,” he replied, because many demons had gone into him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And they begged Jesus repeatedly not to order them to go into the Abyss.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25277Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25277Z\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>A large herd of pigs was feeding there on the hillside. The demons begged Jesus to let them go into the pigs, and he gave them permission.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When the demons came out of the man, they went into the pigs, and the herd rushed down the steep bank into the lake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25279AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25279AA\"></sup> and was drowned.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When those tending the pigs saw what had happened, they ran off and reported this in the town and countryside,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and the people went out to see what had happened. When they came to Jesus, they found the man from whom the demons had gone out, sitting at Jesus’ feet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25281AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25281AB\"></sup> dressed and in his right mind; and they were afraid.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Those who had seen it told the people how the demon-possessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25282AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25282AC\"></sup> man had been cured.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then all the people of the region of the Gerasenes asked Jesus to leave them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25283AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25283AD\"></sup> because they were overcome with fear. So he got into the boat and left.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The man from whom the demons had gone out begged to go with him, but Jesus sent him away, saying,",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“Return home and tell how much God has done for you.”</span> So the man went away and told all over town how much Jesus had done for him.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now when Jesus returned, a crowd welcomed him, for they were all expecting him.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then a man named Jairus, a synagogue leader,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25287AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25287AF\"></sup> came and fell at Jesus’ feet, pleading with him to come to his house",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>because his only daughter, a girl of about twelve, was dying.As Jesus was on his way, the crowds almost crushed him.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And a woman was there who had been subject to bleeding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25289AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25289AG\"></sup> for twelve years, but no one could heal her.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>She came up behind him and touched the edge of his cloak,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25290AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25290AH\"></sup> and immediately her bleeding stopped.",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“Who touched me?”</span> Jesus asked.When they all denied it, Peter said, “Master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25291AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25291AI\"></sup> the people are crowding and pressing against you.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>But Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Someone touched me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25292AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25292AJ\"></sup> I know that power has gone out from me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25292AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25292AK\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Then the woman, seeing that she could not go unnoticed, came trembling and fell at his feet. In the presence of all the people, she told why she had touched him and how she had been instantly healed.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then he said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Daughter, your faith has healed you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25294AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25294AL\"></sup> Go in peace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25294AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25294AM\"></sup></span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>While Jesus was still speaking, someone came from the house of Jairus, the synagogue leader.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25295AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25295AN\"></sup> “Your daughter is dead,” he said. “Don’t bother the teacher anymore.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Hearing this, Jesus said to Jairus, <span class=\"woj\">“Don’t be afraid; just believe, and she will be healed.”</span>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>When he arrived at the house of Jairus, he did not let anyone go in with him except Peter, John and James,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25297AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25297AO\"></sup> and the child’s father and mother.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Meanwhile, all the people were wailing and mourning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25298AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25298AP\"></sup> for her. <span class=\"woj\">“Stop wailing,”</span> Jesus said. <span class=\"woj\">“She is not dead but asleep.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25298AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25298AQ\"></sup></span>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>They laughed at him, knowing that she was dead.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>But he took her by the hand and said, <span class=\"woj\">“My child, get up!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25300AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25300AR\"></sup></span>",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Her spirit returned, and at once she stood up. Then Jesus told them to give her something to eat.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Her parents were astonished, but he ordered them not to tell anyone what had happened.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25302AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25302AS\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>When Jesus had called the Twelve together, he gave them power and authority to drive out all demons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25303C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25303C\"></sup> and to cure diseases,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25303D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25303D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he sent them out to proclaim the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25304E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25304E\"></sup> and to heal the sick.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He told them: <span class=\"woj\">“Take nothing for the journey—no staff, no bag, no bread, no money, no extra shirt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25305F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25305F\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Whatever house you enter, stay there until you leave that town.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If people do not welcome you, leave their town and shake the dust off your feet as a testimony against them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25307G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25307G\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So they set out and went from village to village, proclaiming the good news and healing people everywhere.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25309H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25309H\"></sup> the tetrarch heard about all that was going on. And he was perplexed because some were saying that John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25309I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25309I\"></sup> had been raised from the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25309J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25309J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>others that Elijah had appeared,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25310K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25310K\"></sup> and still others that one of the prophets of long ago had come back to life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25310L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25310L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Herod said, “I beheaded John. Who, then, is this I hear such things about?” And he tried to see him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25311M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25311M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the apostles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25312P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25312P\"></sup> returned, they reported to Jesus what they had done. Then he took them with him and they withdrew by themselves to a town called Bethsaida,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25312Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25312Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>but the crowds learned about it and followed him. He welcomed them and spoke to them about the kingdom of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25313R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25313R\"></sup> and healed those who needed healing.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Late in the afternoon the Twelve came to him and said, “Send the crowd away so they can go to the surrounding villages and countryside and find food and lodging, because we are in a remote place here.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“You give them something to eat.”</span>They answered, “We have only five loaves of bread and two fish—unless we go and buy food for all this crowd.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>(About five thousand men were there.)But he said to his disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“Have them sit down in groups of about fifty each.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The disciples did so, and everyone sat down.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Taking the five loaves and the two fish and looking up to heaven, he gave thanks and broke them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25318S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25318S\"></sup> Then he gave them to the disciples to distribute to the people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They all ate and were satisfied, and the disciples picked up twelve basketfuls of broken pieces that were left over.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Once when Jesus was praying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25320V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25320V\"></sup> in private and his disciples were with him, he asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“Who do the crowds say I am?”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They replied, “Some say John the Baptist;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25321W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25321W\"></sup> others say Elijah; and still others, that one of the prophets of long ago has come back to life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25321X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25321X\"></sup>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“But what about you?”</span> he asked. <span class=\"woj\">“Who do you say I am?”</span>Peter answered, “God’s Messiah.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25322Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25322Y\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Jesus strictly warned them not to tell this to anyone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25323Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25323Z\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And he said, <span class=\"woj\">“The Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25324AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25324AA\"></sup> must suffer many things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25324AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25324AB\"></sup> and be rejected by the elders, the chief priests and the teachers of the law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25324AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25324AC\"></sup> and he must be killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25324AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25324AD\"></sup> and on the third day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25324AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25324AE\"></sup> be raised to life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25324AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25324AF\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he said to them all: <span class=\"woj\">“Whoever wants to be my disciple must deny themselves and take up their cross daily and follow me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25325AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25325AG\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For whoever wants to save their life will lose it, but whoever loses their life for me will save it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25326AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25326AH\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>What good is it for someone to gain the whole world, and yet lose or forfeit their very self?</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Whoever is ashamed of me and my words, the Son of Man will be ashamed of them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25328AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25328AI\"></sup> when he comes in his glory and in the glory of the Father and of the holy angels.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25328AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25328AJ\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Truly I tell you, some who are standing here will not taste death before they see the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>About eight days after Jesus said this, he took Peter, John and James<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25330AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25330AL\"></sup> with him and went up onto a mountain to pray.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25330AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25330AM\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As he was praying, the appearance of his face changed, and his clothes became as bright as a flash of lightning.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Two men, Moses and Elijah, appeared in glorious splendor, talking with Jesus.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They spoke about his departure,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25333AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25333AN\"></sup> which he was about to bring to fulfillment at Jerusalem.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Peter and his companions were very sleepy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25334AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25334AO\"></sup> but when they became fully awake, they saw his glory and the two men standing with him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>As the men were leaving Jesus, Peter said to him, “Master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25335AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25335AP\"></sup> it is good for us to be here. Let us put up three shelters—one for you, one for Moses and one for Elijah.” (He did not know what he was saying.)",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>While he was speaking, a cloud appeared and covered them, and they were afraid as they entered the cloud.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>A voice came from the cloud, saying, “This is my Son, whom I have chosen;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25337AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25337AQ\"></sup> listen to him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25337AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25337AR\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When the voice had spoken, they found that Jesus was alone. The disciples kept this to themselves and did not tell anyone at that time what they had seen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25338AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25338AS\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The next day, when they came down from the mountain, a large crowd met him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>A man in the crowd called out, “Teacher, I beg you to look at my son, for he is my only child.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>A spirit seizes him and he suddenly screams; it throws him into convulsions so that he foams at the mouth. It scarcely ever leaves him and is destroying him.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>I begged your disciples to drive it out, but they could not.”",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“You unbelieving and perverse generation,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25343AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25343AU\"></sup></span> Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“how long shall I stay with you and put up with you? Bring your son here.”</span>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Even while the boy was coming, the demon threw him to the ground in a convulsion. But Jesus rebuked the impure spirit, healed the boy and gave him back to his father.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And they were all amazed at the greatness of God.While everyone was marveling at all that Jesus did, he said to his disciples,",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“Listen carefully to what I am about to tell you: The Son of Man is going to be delivered into the hands of men.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25346AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25346AV\"></sup></span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But they did not understand what this meant. It was hidden from them, so that they did not grasp it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25347AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25347AW\"></sup> and they were afraid to ask him about it.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>An argument started among the disciples as to which of them would be the greatest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25348AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25348AX\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Jesus, knowing their thoughts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25349AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25349AY\"></sup> took a little child and had him stand beside him.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Whoever welcomes this little child in my name welcomes me; and whoever welcomes me welcomes the one who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25350AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25350AZ\"></sup> For it is the one who is least among you all who is the greatest.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25350BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25350BA\"></sup></span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“Master,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25351BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25351BB\"></sup> said John, “we saw someone driving out demons in your name and we tried to stop him, because he is not one of us.”",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>“Do not stop him,”</span> Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“for whoever is not against you is for you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25352BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25352BC\"></sup></span>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>As the time approached for him to be taken up to heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25353BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25353BD\"></sup> Jesus resolutely set out for Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25353BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25353BE\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And he sent messengers on ahead, who went into a Samaritan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25354BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25354BF\"></sup> village to get things ready for him;",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>but the people there did not welcome him, because he was heading for Jerusalem.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>When the disciples James and John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25356BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25356BG\"></sup> saw this, they asked, “Lord, do you want us to call fire down from heaven to destroy them?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25356BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25356BH\"></sup>",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But Jesus turned and rebuked them.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Then he and his disciples went to another village.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>As they were walking along the road,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25359BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25359BJ\"></sup> a man said to him, “I will follow you wherever you go.”",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Foxes have dens and birds have nests, but the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25360BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25360BK\"></sup> has no place to lay his head.”</span>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>He said to another man, <span class=\"woj\">“Follow me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25361BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25361BL\"></sup></span>But he replied, “Lord, first let me go and bury my father.”",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Let the dead bury their own dead, but you go and proclaim the kingdom of God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25362BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25362BM\"></sup></span>",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Still another said, “I will follow you, Lord; but first let me go back and say goodbye to my family.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25363BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25363BN\"></sup>",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“No one who puts a hand to the plow and looks back is fit for service in the kingdom of God.”</span>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>After this the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25365D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25365D\"></sup> appointed seventy-two others<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25365E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25365E\"></sup> and sent them two by two<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25365F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25365F\"></sup> ahead of him to every town and place where he was about to go.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25365G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25365G\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He told them, <span class=\"woj\">“The harvest is plentiful, but the workers are few. Ask the Lord of the harvest, therefore, to send out workers into his harvest field.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25366H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25366H\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Go! I am sending you out like lambs among wolves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25367I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25367I\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Do not take a purse or bag or sandals; and do not greet anyone on the road.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“When you enter a house, first say, ‘Peace to this house.’</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>If someone who promotes peace is there, your peace will rest on them; if not, it will return to you.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Stay there, eating and drinking whatever they give you, for the worker deserves his wages.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25371J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25371J\"></sup> Do not move around from house to house.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“When you enter a town and are welcomed, eat what is offered to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25372K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25372K\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Heal the sick who are there and tell them, ‘The kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25373L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25373L\"></sup> has come near to you.’</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But when you enter a town and are not welcomed, go into its streets and say,</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘Even the dust of your town we wipe from our feet as a warning to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25375M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25375M\"></sup> Yet be sure of this: The kingdom of God has come near.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25375N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25375N\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I tell you, it will be more bearable on that day for Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25376O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25376O\"></sup> than for that town.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25376P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25376P\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Woe to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25377Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25377Q\"></sup> Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the miracles that were performed in you had been performed in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago, sitting in sackcloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25377R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25377R\"></sup> and ashes.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But it will be more bearable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment than for you.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And you, Capernaum,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25379S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25379S\"></sup> will you be lifted to the heavens? No, you will go down to Hades.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Whoever listens to you listens to me; whoever rejects you rejects me; but whoever rejects me rejects him who sent me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25380T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25380T\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The seventy-two<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25381U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25381U\"></sup> returned with joy and said, “Lord, even the demons submit to us in your name.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25381V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25381V\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“I saw Satan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25382W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25382W\"></sup> fall like lightning from heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25382X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25382X\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I have given you authority to trample on snakes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25383Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25383Y\"></sup> and scorpions and to overcome all the power of the enemy; nothing will harm you.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>However, do not rejoice that the spirits submit to you, but rejoice that your names are written in heaven.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25384Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25384Z\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>At that time Jesus, full of joy through the Holy Spirit, said, <span class=\"woj\">“I praise you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because you have hidden these things from the wise and learned, and revealed them to little children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25385AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25385AA\"></sup> Yes, Father, for this is what you were pleased to do.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“All things have been committed to me by my Father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25386AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25386AB\"></sup> No one knows who the Son is except the Father, and no one knows who the Father is except the Son and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25386AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25386AC\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he turned to his disciples and said privately, <span class=\"woj\">“Blessed are the eyes that see what you see.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For I tell you that many prophets and kings wanted to see what you see but did not see it, and to hear what you hear but did not hear it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25388AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25388AD\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>On one occasion an expert in the law stood up to test Jesus. “Teacher,” he asked, “what must I do to inherit eternal life?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25389AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25389AF\"></sup>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“What is written in the Law?”</span> he replied. <span class=\"woj\">“How do you read it?”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He answered, “‘Love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your strength and with all your mind’;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25391AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25391AG\"></sup> and, ‘Love your neighbor as yourself.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25391AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25391AH\"></sup>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“You have answered correctly,”</span> Jesus replied. <span class=\"woj\">“Do this and you will live.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25392AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25392AI\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But he wanted to justify himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25393AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25393AJ\"></sup> so he asked Jesus, “And who is my neighbor?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>In reply Jesus said: <span class=\"woj\">“A man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, when he was attacked by robbers. They stripped him of his clothes, beat him and went away, leaving him half dead.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>A priest happened to be going down the same road, and when he saw the man, he passed by on the other side.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25395AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25395AK\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So too, a Levite, when he came to the place and saw him, passed by on the other side.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But a Samaritan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25397AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25397AL\"></sup> as he traveled, came where the man was; and when he saw him, he took pity on him.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He went to him and bandaged his wounds, pouring on oil and wine. Then he put the man on his own donkey, brought him to an inn and took care of him.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The next day he took out two denarii and gave them to the innkeeper. ‘Look after him,’ he said, ‘and when I return, I will reimburse you for any extra expense you may have.’</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“Which of these three do you think was a neighbor to the man who fell into the hands of robbers?”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The expert in the law replied, “The one who had mercy on him.”Jesus told him, <span class=\"woj\">“Go and do likewise.”</span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>As Jesus and his disciples were on their way, he came to a village where a woman named Martha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25402AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25402AM\"></sup> opened her home to him.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>She had a sister called Mary,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25403AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25403AN\"></sup> who sat at the Lord’s feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25403AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25403AO\"></sup> listening to what he said.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But Martha was distracted by all the preparations that had to be made. She came to him and asked, “Lord, don’t you care<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25404AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25404AP\"></sup> that my sister has left me to do the work by myself? Tell her to help me!”",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Martha, Martha,”</span> the Lord answered, <span class=\"woj\">“you are worried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25405AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25405AQ\"></sup> and upset about many things,</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>but few things are needed—or indeed only one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25406AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25406AR\"></sup> Mary has chosen what is better, and it will not be taken away from her.”</span>"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>One day Jesus was praying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25407C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25407C\"></sup> in a certain place. When he finished, one of his disciples said to him, “Lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25407D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25407D\"></sup> teach us to pray, just as John taught his disciples.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“When you pray, say:</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘Father,</span><span class=\"woj\">hallowed be your name,</span><span class=\"woj\">your kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25408E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25408E\"></sup> come.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Give us each day our daily bread.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Forgive us our sins,</span><span class=\"woj\">for we also forgive everyone who sins against us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25410F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25410F\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">And lead us not into temptation.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25410G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25410G\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Suppose you have a friend, and you go to him at midnight and say, ‘Friend, lend me three loaves of bread;</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>a friend of mine on a journey has come to me, and I have no food to offer him.’</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And suppose the one inside answers, ‘Don’t bother me. The door is already locked, and my children and I are in bed. I can’t get up and give you anything.’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I tell you, even though he will not get up and give you the bread because of friendship, yet because of your shameless audacity he will surely get up and give you as much as you need.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25414H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25414H\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“So I say to you: Ask and it will be given to you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25415I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25415I\"></sup> seek and you will find; knock and the door will be opened to you.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For everyone who asks receives; the one who seeks finds; and to the one who knocks, the door will be opened.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Which of you fathers, if your son asks for a fish, will give him a snake instead?</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Or if he asks for an egg, will give him a scorpion?</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If you then, though you are evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father in heaven give the Holy Spirit to those who ask him!”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jesus was driving out a demon that was mute. When the demon left, the man who had been mute spoke, and the crowd was amazed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25420L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25420L\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But some of them said, “By Beelzebul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25421M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25421M\"></sup> the prince of demons, he is driving out demons.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25421N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25421N\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Others tested him by asking for a sign from heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25422O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25422O\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jesus knew their thoughts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25423P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25423P\"></sup> and said to them: <span class=\"woj\">“Any kingdom divided against itself will be ruined, and a house divided against itself will fall.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If Satan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25424Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25424Q\"></sup> is divided against himself, how can his kingdom stand? I say this because you claim that I drive out demons by Beelzebul.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now if I drive out demons by Beelzebul, by whom do your followers drive them out? So then, they will be your judges.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if I drive out demons by the finger of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25426R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25426R\"></sup> then the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25426S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25426S\"></sup> has come upon you.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“When a strong man, fully armed, guards his own house, his possessions are safe.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But when someone stronger attacks and overpowers him, he takes away the armor in which the man trusted and divides up his plunder.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Whoever is not with me is against me, and whoever does not gather with me scatters.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25429T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25429T\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“When an impure spirit comes out of a person, it goes through arid places seeking rest and does not find it. Then it says, ‘I will return to the house I left.’</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When it arrives, it finds the house swept clean and put in order.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then it goes and takes seven other spirits more wicked than itself, and they go in and live there. And the final condition of that person is worse than the first.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25432U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25432U\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As Jesus was saying these things, a woman in the crowd called out, “Blessed is the mother who gave you birth and nursed you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25433V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25433V\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Blessed rather are those who hear the word of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25434W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25434W\"></sup> and obey it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25434X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25434X\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As the crowds increased, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“This is a wicked generation. It asks for a sign,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25435Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25435Z\"></sup> but none will be given it except the sign of Jonah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25435AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25435AA\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For as Jonah was a sign to the Ninevites, so also will the Son of Man be to this generation.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The Queen of the South will rise at the judgment with the people of this generation and condemn them, for she came from the ends of the earth to listen to Solomon’s wisdom;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25437AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25437AB\"></sup> and now something greater than Solomon is here.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The men of Nineveh will stand up at the judgment with this generation and condemn it, for they repented at the preaching of Jonah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25438AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25438AC\"></sup> and now something greater than Jonah is here.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“No one lights a lamp and puts it in a place where it will be hidden, or under a bowl. Instead they put it on its stand, so that those who come in may see the light.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25439AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25439AE\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Your eye is the lamp of your body. When your eyes are healthy, your whole body also is full of light. But when they are unhealthy, your body also is full of darkness.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>See to it, then, that the light within you is not darkness.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Therefore, if your whole body is full of light, and no part of it dark, it will be just as full of light as when a lamp shines its light on you.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When Jesus had finished speaking, a Pharisee invited him to eat with him; so he went in and reclined at the table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25443AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25443AF\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But the Pharisee was surprised when he noticed that Jesus did not first wash before the meal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25444AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25444AG\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25445AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25445AH\"></sup> said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Now then, you Pharisees clean the outside of the cup and dish, but inside you are full of greed and wickedness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25445AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25445AI\"></sup></span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You foolish people!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25446AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25446AJ\"></sup> Did not the one who made the outside make the inside also?</span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But now as for what is inside you—be generous to the poor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25447AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25447AK\"></sup> and everything will be clean for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25447AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25447AL\"></sup></span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“Woe to you Pharisees, because you give God a tenth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25448AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25448AM\"></sup> of your mint, rue and all other kinds of garden herbs, but you neglect justice and the love of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25448AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25448AN\"></sup> You should have practiced the latter without leaving the former undone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25448AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25448AO\"></sup></span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“Woe to you Pharisees, because you love the most important seats in the synagogues and respectful greetings in the marketplaces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25449AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25449AP\"></sup></span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“Woe to you, because you are like unmarked graves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25450AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25450AQ\"></sup> which people walk over without knowing it.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>One of the experts in the law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25451AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25451AR\"></sup> answered him, “Teacher, when you say these things, you insult us also.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“And you experts in the law, woe to you, because you load people down with burdens they can hardly carry, and you yourselves will not lift one finger to help them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25452AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25452AS\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“Woe to you, because you build tombs for the prophets, and it was your ancestors who killed them.</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>So you testify that you approve of what your ancestors did; they killed the prophets, and you build their tombs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25454AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25454AT\"></sup></span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Because of this, God in his wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25455AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25455AU\"></sup> said, ‘I will send them prophets and apostles, some of whom they will kill and others they will persecute.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25455AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25455AV\"></sup></span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Therefore this generation will be held responsible for the blood of all the prophets that has been shed since the beginning of the world,</span>",
			"51": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>from the blood of Abel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25457AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25457AW\"></sup> to the blood of Zechariah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25457AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25457AX\"></sup> who was killed between the altar and the sanctuary. Yes, I tell you, this generation will be held responsible for it all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25457AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25457AY\"></sup></span>",
			"52": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>“Woe to you experts in the law, because you have taken away the key to knowledge. You yourselves have not entered, and you have hindered those who were entering.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25458AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25458AZ\"></sup></span>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>When Jesus went outside, the Pharisees and the teachers of the law began to oppose him fiercely and to besiege him with questions,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>waiting to catch him in something he might say.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25460BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25460BA\"></sup>"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Meanwhile, when a crowd of many thousands had gathered, so that they were trampling on one another, Jesus began to speak first to his disciples, saying: <span class=\"woj\">“Be on your guard against the yeast of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25461B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25461B\"></sup></span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There is nothing concealed that will not be disclosed, or hidden that will not be made known.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25462C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25462C\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>What you have said in the dark will be heard in the daylight, and what you have whispered in the ear in the inner rooms will be proclaimed from the roofs.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I tell you, my friends,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25464D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25464D\"></sup> do not be afraid of those who kill the body and after that can do no more.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But I will show you whom you should fear: Fear him who, after your body has been killed, has authority to throw you into hell. Yes, I tell you, fear him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25465E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25465E\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Are not five sparrows sold for two pennies? Yet not one of them is forgotten by God.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Indeed, the very hairs of your head are all numbered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25467F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25467F\"></sup> Don’t be afraid; you are worth more than many sparrows.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25467G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25467G\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“I tell you, whoever publicly acknowledges me before others, the Son of Man will also acknowledge before the angels of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25468H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25468H\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But whoever disowns me before others will be disowned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25469I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25469I\"></sup> before the angels of God.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And everyone who speaks a word against the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25470J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25470J\"></sup> will be forgiven, but anyone who blasphemes against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25470K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25470K\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“When you are brought before synagogues, rulers and authorities, do not worry about how you will defend yourselves or what you will say,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25471L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25471L\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>for the Holy Spirit will teach you at that time what you should say.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25472M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25472M\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Someone in the crowd said to him, “Teacher, tell my brother to divide the inheritance with me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Man, who appointed me a judge or an arbiter between you?”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Watch out! Be on your guard against all kinds of greed; life does not consist in an abundance of possessions.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25475N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25475N\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he told them this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“The ground of a certain rich man yielded an abundant harvest.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He thought to himself, ‘What shall I do? I have no place to store my crops.’</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Then he said, ‘This is what I’ll do. I will tear down my barns and build bigger ones, and there I will store my surplus grain.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And I’ll say to myself, “You have plenty of grain laid up for many years. Take life easy; eat, drink and be merry.”’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“But God said to him, ‘You fool!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25480O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25480O\"></sup> This very night your life will be demanded from you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25480P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25480P\"></sup> Then who will get what you have prepared for yourself?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25480Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25480Q\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“This is how it will be with whoever stores up things for themselves but is not rich toward God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25481R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25481R\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Jesus said to his disciples: <span class=\"woj\">“Therefore I tell you, do not worry about your life, what you will eat; or about your body, what you will wear.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For life is more than food, and the body more than clothes.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Consider the ravens: They do not sow or reap, they have no storeroom or barn; yet God feeds them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25484T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25484T\"></sup> And how much more valuable you are than birds!</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Who of you by worrying can add a single hour to your life?</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Since you cannot do this very little thing, why do you worry about the rest?</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Consider how the wild flowers grow. They do not labor or spin. Yet I tell you, not even Solomon in all his splendor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25487U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25487U\"></sup> was dressed like one of these.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>If that is how God clothes the grass of the field, which is here today, and tomorrow is thrown into the fire, how much more will he clothe you—you of little faith!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25488V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25488V\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And do not set your heart on what you will eat or drink; do not worry about it.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For the pagan world runs after all such things, and your Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25490W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25490W\"></sup> knows that you need them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25490X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25490X\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But seek his kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25491Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25491Y\"></sup> and these things will be given to you as well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25491Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25491Z\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Do not be afraid,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25492AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25492AA\"></sup> little flock, for your Father has been pleased to give you the kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25492AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25492AB\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Sell your possessions and give to the poor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25493AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25493AC\"></sup> Provide purses for yourselves that will not wear out, a treasure in heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25493AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25493AD\"></sup> that will never fail, where no thief comes near and no moth destroys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25493AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25493AE\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25494AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25494AF\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“Be dressed ready for service and keep your lamps burning,</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>like servants waiting for their master to return from a wedding banquet, so that when he comes and knocks they can immediately open the door for him.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>It will be good for those servants whose master finds them watching when he comes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25497AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25497AI\"></sup> Truly I tell you, he will dress himself to serve, will have them recline at the table and will come and wait on them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25497AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25497AJ\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>It will be good for those servants whose master finds them ready, even if he comes in the middle of the night or toward daybreak.</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But understand this: If the owner of the house had known at what hour the thief<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25499AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25499AK\"></sup> was coming, he would not have let his house be broken into.</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You also must be ready,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25500AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25500AL\"></sup> because the Son of Man will come at an hour when you do not expect him.”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Peter asked, “Lord, are you telling this parable to us, or to everyone?”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25502AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25502AM\"></sup> answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Who then is the faithful and wise manager, whom the master puts in charge of his servants to give them their food allowance at the proper time?</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>It will be good for that servant whom the master finds doing so when he returns.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Truly I tell you, he will put him in charge of all his possessions.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But suppose the servant says to himself, ‘My master is taking a long time in coming,’ and he then begins to beat the other servants, both men and women, and to eat and drink and get drunk.</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The master of that servant will come on a day when he does not expect him and at an hour he is not aware of.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25506AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25506AN\"></sup> He will cut him to pieces and assign him a place with the unbelievers.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“The servant who knows the master’s will and does not get ready or does not do what the master wants will be beaten with many blows.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25507AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25507AO\"></sup></span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>But the one who does not know and does things deserving punishment will be beaten with few blows.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25508AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25508AP\"></sup> From everyone who has been given much, much will be demanded; and from the one who has been entrusted with much, much more will be asked.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“I have come to bring fire on the earth, and how I wish it were already kindled!</span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But I have a baptism<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25510AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25510AR\"></sup> to undergo, and what constraint I am under until it is completed!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25510AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25510AS\"></sup></span>",
			"51": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Do you think I came to bring peace on earth? No, I tell you, but division.</span>",
			"52": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>From now on there will be five in one family divided against each other, three against two and two against three.</span>",
			"53": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>They will be divided, father against son and son against father, mother against daughter and daughter against mother, mother-in-law against daughter-in-law and daughter-in-law against mother-in-law.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25513AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25513AT\"></sup></span>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>He said to the crowd: <span class=\"woj\">“When you see a cloud rising in the west, immediately you say, ‘It’s going to rain,’ and it does.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25514AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25514AU\"></sup></span>",
			"55": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And when the south wind blows, you say, ‘It’s going to be hot,’ and it is.</span>",
			"56": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Hypocrites! You know how to interpret the appearance of the earth and the sky. How is it that you don’t know how to interpret this present time?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25516AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25516AV\"></sup></span>",
			"57": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>“Why don’t you judge for yourselves what is right?</span>",
			"58": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>As you are going with your adversary to the magistrate, try hard to be reconciled on the way, or your adversary may drag you off to the judge, and the judge turn you over to the officer, and the officer throw you into prison.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25518AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25518AW\"></sup></span>",
			"59": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>I tell you, you will not get out until you have paid the last penny.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25519AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25519AX\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Now there were some present at that time who told Jesus about the Galileans whose blood Pilate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25520A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25520A\"></sup> had mixed with their sacrifices.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you think that these Galileans were worse sinners than all the other Galileans because they suffered this way?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25521B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25521B\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I tell you, no! But unless you repent, you too will all perish.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Or those eighteen who died when the tower in Siloam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25523C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25523C\"></sup> fell on them—do you think they were more guilty than all the others living in Jerusalem?</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I tell you, no! But unless you repent,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25524D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25524D\"></sup> you too will all perish.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he told this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“A man had a fig tree growing in his vineyard, and he went to look for fruit on it but did not find any.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25525E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25525E\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he said to the man who took care of the vineyard, ‘For three years now I’ve been coming to look for fruit on this fig tree and haven’t found any. Cut it down!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25526F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25526F\"></sup> Why should it use up the soil?’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘Sir,’ the man replied, ‘leave it alone for one more year, and I’ll dig around it and fertilize it.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If it bears fruit next year, fine! If not, then cut it down.’”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On a Sabbath Jesus was teaching in one of the synagogues,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25529G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25529G\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and a woman was there who had been crippled by a spirit for eighteen years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25530H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25530H\"></sup> She was bent over and could not straighten up at all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Jesus saw her, he called her forward and said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Woman, you are set free from your infirmity.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then he put his hands on her,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25532I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25532I\"></sup> and immediately she straightened up and praised God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Indignant because Jesus had healed on the Sabbath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25533J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25533J\"></sup> the synagogue leader<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25533K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25533K\"></sup> said to the people, “There are six days for work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25533L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25533L\"></sup> So come and be healed on those days, not on the Sabbath.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The Lord answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“You hypocrites! Doesn’t each of you on the Sabbath untie your ox or donkey from the stall and lead it out to give it water?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25534M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25534M\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then should not this woman, a daughter of Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25535N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25535N\"></sup> whom Satan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25535O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25535O\"></sup> has kept bound for eighteen long years, be set free on the Sabbath day from what bound her?”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he said this, all his opponents were humiliated,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25536P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25536P\"></sup> but the people were delighted with all the wonderful things he was doing.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jesus asked, <span class=\"woj\">“What is the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25537S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25537S\"></sup> like?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25537T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25537T\"></sup> What shall I compare it to?</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It is like a mustard seed, which a man took and planted in his garden. It grew and became a tree,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25538U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25538U\"></sup> and the birds perched in its branches.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25538V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25538V\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Again he asked, <span class=\"woj\">“What shall I compare the kingdom of God to?</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It is like yeast that a woman took and mixed into about sixty pounds of flour until it worked all through the dough.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25540W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25540W\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Jesus went through the towns and villages, teaching as he made his way to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25541X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25541X\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Someone asked him, “Lord, are only a few people going to be saved?”He said to them,",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Make every effort to enter through the narrow door,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25543Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25543Y\"></sup> because many, I tell you, will try to enter and will not be able to.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Once the owner of the house gets up and closes the door, you will stand outside knocking and pleading, ‘Sir, open the door for us.’</span><span class=\"woj\">“But he will answer, ‘I don’t know you or where you come from.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25544Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25544Z\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Then you will say, ‘We ate and drank with you, and you taught in our streets.’</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But he will reply, ‘I don’t know you or where you come from. Away from me, all you evildoers!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25546AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25546AA\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“There will be weeping there, and gnashing of teeth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25547AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25547AB\"></sup> when you see Abraham, Isaac and Jacob and all the prophets in the kingdom of God, but you yourselves thrown out.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>People will come from east and west<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25548AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25548AC\"></sup> and north and south, and will take their places at the feast in the kingdom of God.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Indeed there are those who are last who will be first, and first who will be last.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25549AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25549AD\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>At that time some Pharisees came to Jesus and said to him, “Leave this place and go somewhere else. Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25550AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25550AG\"></sup> wants to kill you.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Go tell that fox, ‘I will keep on driving out demons and healing people today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will reach my goal.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25551AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25551AH\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In any case, I must press on today and tomorrow and the next day—for surely no prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25552AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25552AI\"></sup> can die outside Jerusalem!</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Jerusalem, Jerusalem, you who kill the prophets and stone those sent to you, how often I have longed to gather your children together, as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25553AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25553AJ\"></sup> and you were not willing.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Look, your house is left to you desolate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25554AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25554AK\"></sup> I tell you, you will not see me again until you say, ‘Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25554AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25554AL\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>One Sabbath, when Jesus went to eat in the house of a prominent Pharisee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25555B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25555B\"></sup> he was being carefully watched.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25555C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25555C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There in front of him was a man suffering from abnormal swelling of his body.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jesus asked the Pharisees and experts in the law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25557D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25557D\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">“Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath or not?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25557E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25557E\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But they remained silent. So taking hold of the man, he healed him and sent him on his way.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“If one of you has a child or an ox that falls into a well on the Sabbath day, will you not immediately pull it out?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25559F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25559F\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they had nothing to say.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he noticed how the guests picked the places of honor at the table,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25561G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25561G\"></sup> he told them this parable:",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“When someone invites you to a wedding feast, do not take the place of honor, for a person more distinguished than you may have been invited.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If so, the host who invited both of you will come and say to you, ‘Give this person your seat.’ Then, humiliated, you will have to take the least important place.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But when you are invited, take the lowest place, so that when your host comes, he will say to you, ‘Friend, move up to a better place.’ Then you will be honored in the presence of all the other guests.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For all those who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those who humble themselves will be exalted.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25565H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25565H\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Jesus said to his host, <span class=\"woj\">“When you give a luncheon or dinner, do not invite your friends, your brothers or sisters, your relatives, or your rich neighbors; if you do, they may invite you back and so you will be repaid.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But when you give a banquet, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, the blind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25567I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25567I\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and you will be blessed. Although they cannot repay you, you will be repaid at the resurrection of the righteous.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25568J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25568J\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When one of those at the table with him heard this, he said to Jesus, “Blessed is the one who will eat at the feast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25569L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25569L\"></sup> in the kingdom of God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25569M\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jesus replied: <span class=\"woj\">“A certain man was preparing a great banquet and invited many guests.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>At the time of the banquet he sent his servant to tell those who had been invited, ‘Come, for everything is now ready.’</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“But they all alike began to make excuses. The first said, ‘I have just bought a field, and I must go and see it. Please excuse me.’</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Another said, ‘I have just bought five yoke of oxen, and I’m on my way to try them out. Please excuse me.’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Still another said, ‘I just got married, so I can’t come.’</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“The servant came back and reported this to his master. Then the owner of the house became angry and ordered his servant, ‘Go out quickly into the streets and alleys of the town and bring in the poor, the crippled, the blind and the lame.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25575N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25575N\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘Sir,’ the servant said, ‘what you ordered has been done, but there is still room.’</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Then the master told his servant, ‘Go out to the roads and country lanes and compel them to come in, so that my house will be full.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I tell you, not one of those who were invited will get a taste of my banquet.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25578O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25578O\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Large crowds were traveling with Jesus, and turning to them he said:",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“If anyone comes to me and does not hate father and mother, wife and children, brothers and sisters—yes, even their own life—such a person cannot be my disciple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25580P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25580P\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And whoever does not carry their cross and follow me cannot be my disciple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25581Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25581Q\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Suppose one of you wants to build a tower. Won’t you first sit down and estimate the cost to see if you have enough money to complete it?</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For if you lay the foundation and are not able to finish it, everyone who sees it will ridicule you,</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>saying, ‘This person began to build and wasn’t able to finish.’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Or suppose a king is about to go to war against another king. Won’t he first sit down and consider whether he is able with ten thousand men to oppose the one coming against him with twenty thousand?</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>If he is not able, he will send a delegation while the other is still a long way off and will ask for terms of peace.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the same way, those of you who do not give up everything you have cannot be my disciples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25587R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25587R\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Salt is good, but if it loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25588S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25588S\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>It is fit neither for the soil nor for the manure pile; it is thrown out.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25589T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25589T\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">“Whoever has ears to hear, let them hear.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25589U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25589U\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Now the tax collectors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25590B\"></sup> and sinners were all gathering around to hear Jesus.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But the Pharisees and the teachers of the law muttered, “This man welcomes sinners and eats with them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25591C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25591C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Jesus told them this parable:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25592D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25592D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Suppose one of you has a hundred sheep and loses one of them. Doesn’t he leave the ninety-nine in the open country and go after the lost sheep until he finds it?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25593E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25593E\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when he finds it, he joyfully puts it on his shoulders</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and goes home. Then he calls his friends and neighbors together and says, ‘Rejoice with me; I have found my lost sheep.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25595F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25595F\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I tell you that in the same way there will be more rejoicing in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who do not need to repent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25596G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25596G\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Or suppose a woman has ten silver coins and loses one. Doesn’t she light a lamp, sweep the house and search carefully until she finds it?</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And when she finds it, she calls her friends and neighbors together and says, ‘Rejoice with me; I have found my lost coin.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25598H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25598H\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the same way, I tell you, there is rejoicing in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner who repents.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25599I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25599I\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jesus continued: <span class=\"woj\">“There was a man who had two sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25600J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25600J\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The younger one said to his father, ‘Father, give me my share of the estate.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25601K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25601K\"></sup> So he divided his property<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25601L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25601L\"></sup> between them.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Not long after that, the younger son got together all he had, set off for a distant country and there squandered his wealth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25602M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25602M\"></sup> in wild living.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After he had spent everything, there was a severe famine in that whole country, and he began to be in need.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So he went and hired himself out to a citizen of that country, who sent him to his fields to feed pigs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25604N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25604N\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He longed to fill his stomach with the pods that the pigs were eating, but no one gave him anything.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“When he came to his senses, he said, ‘How many of my father’s hired servants have food to spare, and here I am starving to death!</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will set out and go back to my father and say to him: Father, I have sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25607O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25607O\"></sup> against heaven and against you.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I am no longer worthy to be called your son; make me like one of your hired servants.’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So he got up and went to his father.</span><span class=\"woj\">“But while he was still a long way off, his father saw him and was filled with compassion for him; he ran to his son, threw his arms around him and kissed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25609P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25609P\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“The son said to him, ‘Father, I have sinned against heaven and against you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25610Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25610Q\"></sup> I am no longer worthy to be called your son.’</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“But the father said to his servants, ‘Quick! Bring the best robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25611R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25611R\"></sup> and put it on him. Put a ring on his finger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25611S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25611S\"></sup> and sandals on his feet.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Bring the fattened calf and kill it. Let’s have a feast and celebrate.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For this son of mine was dead and is alive again;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25613T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25613T\"></sup> he was lost and is found.’ So they began to celebrate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25613U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25613U\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Meanwhile, the older son was in the field. When he came near the house, he heard music and dancing.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So he called one of the servants and asked him what was going on.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘Your brother has come,’ he replied, ‘and your father has killed the fattened calf because he has him back safe and sound.’</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“The older brother became angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25617V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25617V\"></sup> and refused to go in. So his father went out and pleaded with him.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But he answered his father, ‘Look! All these years I’ve been slaving for you and never disobeyed your orders. Yet you never gave me even a young goat so I could celebrate with my friends.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But when this son of yours who has squandered your property<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25619W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25619W\"></sup> with prostitutes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25619X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25619X\"></sup> comes home, you kill the fattened calf for him!’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“‘My son,’ the father said, ‘you are always with me, and everything I have is yours.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But we had to celebrate and be glad, because this brother of yours was dead and is alive again; he was lost and is found.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25621Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25621Y\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Jesus told his disciples: <span class=\"woj\">“There was a rich man whose manager was accused of wasting his possessions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25622A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25622A\"></sup></span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So he called him in and asked him, ‘What is this I hear about you? Give an account of your management, because you cannot be manager any longer.’</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“The manager said to himself, ‘What shall I do now? My master is taking away my job. I’m not strong enough to dig, and I’m ashamed to beg—</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I know what I’ll do so that, when I lose my job here, people will welcome me into their houses.’</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“So he called in each one of his master’s debtors. He asked the first, ‘How much do you owe my master?’</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘Nine hundred gallons of olive oil,’ he replied.</span><span class=\"woj\">“The manager told him, ‘Take your bill, sit down quickly, and make it four hundred and fifty.’</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Then he asked the second, ‘And how much do you owe?’</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘A thousand bushels of wheat,’ he replied.</span><span class=\"woj\">“He told him, ‘Take your bill and make it eight hundred.’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“The master commended the dishonest manager because he had acted shrewdly. For the people of this world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25629B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25629B\"></sup> are more shrewd<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25629C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25629C\"></sup> in dealing with their own kind than are the people of the light.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25629D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25629D\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I tell you, use worldly wealth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25630E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25630E\"></sup> to gain friends for yourselves, so that when it is gone, you will be welcomed into eternal dwellings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25630F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25630F\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Whoever can be trusted with very little can also be trusted with much,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25631G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25631G\"></sup> and whoever is dishonest with very little will also be dishonest with much.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So if you have not been trustworthy in handling worldly wealth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25632H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25632H\"></sup> who will trust you with true riches?</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And if you have not been trustworthy with someone else’s property, who will give you property of your own?</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“No one can serve two masters. Either you will hate the one and love the other, or you will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and money.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25634I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25634I\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Pharisees, who loved money,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25635J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25635J\"></sup> heard all this and were sneering at Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25635K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25635K\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You are the ones who justify yourselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25636L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25636L\"></sup> in the eyes of others, but God knows your hearts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25636M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25636M\"></sup> What people value highly is detestable in God’s sight.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“The Law and the Prophets were proclaimed until John.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25637N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25637N\"></sup> Since that time, the good news of the kingdom of God is being preached,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25637O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25637O\"></sup> and everyone is forcing their way into it.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It is easier for heaven and earth to disappear than for the least stroke of a pen to drop out of the Law.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25638P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25638P\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Anyone who divorces his wife and marries another woman commits adultery, and the man who marries a divorced woman commits adultery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25639Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25639Q\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“There was a rich man who was dressed in purple and fine linen and lived in luxury every day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25640R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25640R\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>At his gate was laid a beggar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25641S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25641S\"></sup> named Lazarus, covered with sores</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and longing to eat what fell from the rich man’s table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25642T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25642T\"></sup> Even the dogs came and licked his sores.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“The time came when the beggar died and the angels carried him to Abraham’s side. The rich man also died and was buried.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In Hades, where he was in torment, he looked up and saw Abraham far away, with Lazarus by his side.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So he called to him, ‘Father Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25645U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25645U\"></sup> have pity on me and send Lazarus to dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my tongue, because I am in agony in this fire.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25645V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25645V\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“But Abraham replied, ‘Son, remember that in your lifetime you received your good things, while Lazarus received bad things,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25646W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25646W\"></sup> but now he is comforted here and you are in agony.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25646X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25646X\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And besides all this, between us and you a great chasm has been set in place, so that those who want to go from here to you cannot, nor can anyone cross over from there to us.’</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“He answered, ‘Then I beg you, father, send Lazarus to my family,</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>for I have five brothers. Let him warn them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25649Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25649Y\"></sup> so that they will not also come to this place of torment.’</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Abraham replied, ‘They have Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25650Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25650Z\"></sup> and the Prophets;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25650AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25650AA\"></sup> let them listen to them.’</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“‘No, father Abraham,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25651AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25651AB\"></sup> he said, ‘but if someone from the dead goes to them, they will repent.’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“He said to him, ‘If they do not listen to Moses and the Prophets, they will not be convinced even if someone rises from the dead.’”</span>"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Jesus said to his disciples: <span class=\"woj\">“Things that cause people to stumble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25653A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25653A\"></sup> are bound to come, but woe to anyone through whom they come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25653B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25653B\"></sup></span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It would be better for them to be thrown into the sea with a millstone tied around their neck than to cause one of these little ones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25654C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25654C\"></sup> to stumble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25654D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25654D\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So watch yourselves.</span><span class=\"woj\">“If your brother or sister sins against you, rebuke them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25655E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25655E\"></sup> and if they repent, forgive them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25655F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25655F\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Even if they sin against you seven times in a day and seven times come back to you saying ‘I repent,’ you must forgive them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25656G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25656G\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The apostles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25657H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25657H\"></sup> said to the Lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25657I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25657I\"></sup> “Increase our faith!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“If you have faith as small as a mustard seed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25658J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25658J\"></sup> you can say to this mulberry tree, ‘Be uprooted and planted in the sea,’ and it will obey you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25658K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25658K\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Suppose one of you has a servant plowing or looking after the sheep. Will he say to the servant when he comes in from the field, ‘Come along now and sit down to eat’?</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Won’t he rather say, ‘Prepare my supper, get yourself ready and wait on me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25660L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25660L\"></sup> while I eat and drink; after that you may eat and drink’?</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Will he thank the servant because he did what he was told to do?</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So you also, when you have done everything you were told to do, should say, ‘We are unworthy servants; we have only done our duty.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25662M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25662M\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now on his way to Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25663N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25663N\"></sup> Jesus traveled along the border between Samaria and Galilee.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25663O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25663O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As he was going into a village, ten men who had leprosy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25664P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25664P\"></sup> met him. They stood at a distance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25664Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25664Q\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and called out in a loud voice, “Jesus, Master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25665R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25665R\"></sup> have pity on us!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When he saw them, he said, <span class=\"woj\">“Go, show yourselves to the priests.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25666S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25666S\"></sup></span> And as they went, they were cleansed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>One of them, when he saw he was healed, came back, praising God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25667T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25667T\"></sup> in a loud voice.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He threw himself at Jesus’ feet and thanked him—and he was a Samaritan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25668U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25668U\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jesus asked, <span class=\"woj\">“Were not all ten cleansed? Where are the other nine?</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Has no one returned to give praise to God except this foreigner?”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then he said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Rise and go; your faith has made you well.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25671V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25671V\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Once, on being asked by the Pharisees when the kingdom of God would come,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25672X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25672X\"></sup> Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“The coming of the kingdom of God is not something that can be observed,</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>nor will people say, ‘Here it is,’ or ‘There it is,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25673Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25673Y\"></sup> because the kingdom of God is in your midst.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then he said to his disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“The time is coming when you will long to see one of the days of the Son of Man,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25674Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25674Z\"></sup> but you will not see it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25674AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25674AA\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>People will tell you, ‘There he is!’ or ‘Here he is!’ Do not go running off after them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25675AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25675AB\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For the Son of Man in his day will be like the lightning,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25676AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25676AC\"></sup> which flashes and lights up the sky from one end to the other.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But first he must suffer many things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25677AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25677AD\"></sup> and be rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25677AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25677AE\"></sup> by this generation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25677AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25677AF\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Just as it was in the days of Noah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25678AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25678AG\"></sup> so also will it be in the days of the Son of Man.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>People were eating, drinking, marrying and being given in marriage up to the day Noah entered the ark. Then the flood came and destroyed them all.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“It was the same in the days of Lot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25680AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25680AH\"></sup> People were eating and drinking, buying and selling, planting and building.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But the day Lot left Sodom, fire and sulfur rained down from heaven and destroyed them all.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“It will be just like this on the day the Son of Man is revealed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25682AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25682AI\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>On that day no one who is on the housetop, with possessions inside, should go down to get them. Likewise, no one in the field should go back for anything.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25683AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25683AJ\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Remember Lot’s wife!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25684AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25684AK\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Whoever tries to keep their life will lose it, and whoever loses their life will preserve it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25685AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25685AL\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>I tell you, on that night two people will be in one bed; one will be taken and the other left.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Two women will be grinding grain together; one will be taken and the other left.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25687AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25687AM\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">[36] </sup></span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“Where, Lord?” they asked.He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Where there is a dead body, there the vultures will gather.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25689AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25689AN\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Then Jesus told his disciples a parable to show them that they should always pray and not give up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25690A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25690A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said: <span class=\"woj\">“In a certain town there was a judge who neither feared God nor cared what people thought.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And there was a widow in that town who kept coming to him with the plea, ‘Grant me justice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25692B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25692B\"></sup> against my adversary.’</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“For some time he refused. But finally he said to himself, ‘Even though I don’t fear God or care what people think,</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>yet because this widow keeps bothering me, I will see that she gets justice, so that she won’t eventually come and attack me!’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25694C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25694C\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25695D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25695D\"></sup> said, <span class=\"woj\">“Listen to what the unjust judge says.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And will not God bring about justice for his chosen ones, who cry out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25696E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25696E\"></sup> to him day and night? Will he keep putting them off?</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I tell you, he will see that they get justice, and quickly. However, when the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25697F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25697F\"></sup> comes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25697G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25697G\"></sup> will he find faith on the earth?”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>To some who were confident of their own righteousness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25698H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25698H\"></sup> and looked down on everyone else,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25698I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25698I\"></sup> Jesus told this parable:",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Two men went up to the temple to pray,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25699J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25699J\"></sup> one a Pharisee and the other a tax collector.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Pharisee stood by himself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25700K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25700K\"></sup> and prayed: ‘God, I thank you that I am not like other people—robbers, evildoers, adulterers—or even like this tax collector.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I fast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25701L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25701L\"></sup> twice a week and give a tenth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25701M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25701M\"></sup> of all I get.’</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“But the tax collector stood at a distance. He would not even look up to heaven, but beat his breast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25702N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25702N\"></sup> and said, ‘God, have mercy on me, a sinner.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25702O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25702O\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“I tell you that this man, rather than the other, went home justified before God. For all those who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those who humble themselves will be exalted.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25703P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25703P\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>People were also bringing babies to Jesus for him to place his hands on them. When the disciples saw this, they rebuked them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But Jesus called the children to him and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Let the little children come to me, and do not hinder them, for the kingdom of God belongs to such as these.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Truly I tell you, anyone who will not receive the kingdom of God like a little child<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25706R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25706R\"></sup> will never enter it.”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>A certain ruler asked him, “Good teacher, what must I do to inherit eternal life?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25707T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25707T\"></sup>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Why do you call me good?”</span> Jesus answered. <span class=\"woj\">“No one is good—except God alone.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You know the commandments: ‘You shall not commit adultery, you shall not murder, you shall not steal, you shall not give false testimony, honor your father and mother.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25709U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25709U\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“All these I have kept since I was a boy,” he said.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Jesus heard this, he said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“You still lack one thing. Sell everything you have and give to the poor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25711V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25711V\"></sup> and you will have treasure in heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25711W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25711W\"></sup> Then come, follow me.”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When he heard this, he became very sad, because he was very wealthy.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Jesus looked at him and said, <span class=\"woj\">“How hard it is for the rich to enter the kingdom of God!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25713X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25713X\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Indeed, it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for someone who is rich to enter the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who heard this asked, “Who then can be saved?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“What is impossible with man is possible with God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25716Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25716Y\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Peter said to him, “We have left all we had to follow you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25717Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25717Z\"></sup>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Truly I tell you,”</span> Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“no one who has left home or wife or brothers or sisters or parents or children for the sake of the kingdom of God</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>will fail to receive many times as much in this age, and in the age to come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25719AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25719AA\"></sup> eternal life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25719AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25719AB\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jesus took the Twelve aside and told them, <span class=\"woj\">“We are going up to Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25720AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25720AD\"></sup> and everything that is written by the prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25720AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25720AE\"></sup> about the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25720AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25720AF\"></sup> will be fulfilled.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He will be delivered over to the Gentiles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25721AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25721AG\"></sup> They will mock him, insult him and spit on him;</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>they will flog him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25722AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25722AH\"></sup> and kill him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25722AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25722AI\"></sup> On the third day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25722AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25722AJ\"></sup> he will rise again.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25722AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25722AK\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The disciples did not understand any of this. Its meaning was hidden from them, and they did not know what he was talking about.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25723AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25723AL\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>As Jesus approached Jericho,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25724AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25724AN\"></sup> a blind man was sitting by the roadside begging.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When he heard the crowd going by, he asked what was happening.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They told him, “Jesus of Nazareth is passing by.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25726AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25726AO\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He called out, “Jesus, Son of David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25727AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25727AP\"></sup> have mercy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25727AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25727AQ\"></sup> on me!”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Those who led the way rebuked him and told him to be quiet, but he shouted all the more, “Son of David, have mercy on me!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25728AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25728AR\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Jesus stopped and ordered the man to be brought to him. When he came near, Jesus asked him,",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“What do you want me to do for you?”</span>“Lord, I want to see,” he replied.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Receive your sight; your faith has healed you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25731AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25731AS\"></sup></span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Immediately he received his sight and followed Jesus, praising God. When all the people saw it, they also praised God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25732AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25732AT\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Jesus entered Jericho<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25733A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25733A\"></sup> and was passing through.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A man was there by the name of Zacchaeus; he was a chief tax collector and was wealthy.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He wanted to see who Jesus was, but because he was short he could not see over the crowd.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he ran ahead and climbed a sycamore-fig<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25736B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25736B\"></sup> tree to see him, since Jesus was coming that way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25736C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25736C\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Jesus reached the spot, he looked up and said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Zacchaeus, come down immediately. I must stay at your house today.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he came down at once and welcomed him gladly.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All the people saw this and began to mutter, “He has gone to be the guest of a sinner.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25739D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25739D\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Zacchaeus stood up and said to the Lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25740E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25740E\"></sup> “Look, Lord! Here and now I give half of my possessions to the poor, and if I have cheated anybody out of anything,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25740F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25740F\"></sup> I will pay back four times the amount.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25740G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25740G\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Today salvation has come to this house, because this man, too, is a son of Abraham.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25741H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25741H\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For the Son of Man came to seek and to save the lost.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25742I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25742I\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>While they were listening to this, he went on to tell them a parable, because he was near Jerusalem and the people thought that the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25743K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25743K\"></sup> was going to appear at once.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25743L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25743L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said: <span class=\"woj\">“A man of noble birth went to a distant country to have himself appointed king and then to return.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he called ten of his servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25745M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25745M\"></sup> and gave them ten minas. ‘Put this money to work,’ he said, ‘until I come back.’</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But his subjects hated him and sent a delegation after him to say, ‘We don’t want this man to be our king.’</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“He was made king, however, and returned home. Then he sent for the servants to whom he had given the money, in order to find out what they had gained with it.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“The first one came and said, ‘Sir, your mina has earned ten more.’</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘Well done, my good servant!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25749N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25749N\"></sup> his master replied. ‘Because you have been trustworthy in a very small matter, take charge of ten cities.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25749O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25749O\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“The second came and said, ‘Sir, your mina has earned five more.’</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“His master answered, ‘You take charge of five cities.’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Then another servant came and said, ‘Sir, here is your mina; I have kept it laid away in a piece of cloth.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I was afraid of you, because you are a hard man. You take out what you did not put in and reap what you did not sow.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25753P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25753P\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“His master replied, ‘I will judge you by your own words,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25754Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25754Q\"></sup> you wicked servant! You knew, did you, that I am a hard man, taking out what I did not put in, and reaping what I did not sow?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25754R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25754R\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Why then didn’t you put my money on deposit, so that when I came back, I could have collected it with interest?’</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Then he said to those standing by, ‘Take his mina away from him and give it to the one who has ten minas.’</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“‘Sir,’ they said, ‘he already has ten!’</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“He replied, ‘I tell you that to everyone who has, more will be given, but as for the one who has nothing, even what they have will be taken away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25758S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25758S\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But those enemies of mine who did not want me to be king over them—bring them here and kill them in front of me.’”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>After Jesus had said this, he went on ahead, going up to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25760V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25760V\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As he approached Bethphage and Bethany<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25761W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25761W\"></sup> at the hill called the Mount of Olives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25761X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25761X\"></sup> he sent two of his disciples, saying to them,",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“Go to the village ahead of you, and as you enter it, you will find a colt tied there, which no one has ever ridden. Untie it and bring it here.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If anyone asks you, ‘Why are you untying it?’ say, ‘The Lord needs it.’”</span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Those who were sent ahead went and found it just as he had told them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25764Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25764Y\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>As they were untying the colt, its owners asked them, “Why are you untying the colt?”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>They replied, “The Lord needs it.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They brought it to Jesus, threw their cloaks on the colt and put Jesus on it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As he went along, people spread their cloaks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25768Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25768Z\"></sup> on the road.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When he came near the place where the road goes down the Mount of Olives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25769AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25769AA\"></sup> the whole crowd of disciples began joyfully to praise God in loud voices for all the miracles they had seen:",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Blessed is the king who comes in the name of the Lord!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25770AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25770AB\"></sup>“Peace in heaven and glory in the highest!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25770AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25770AC\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Some of the Pharisees in the crowd said to Jesus, “Teacher, rebuke your disciples!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25771AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25771AD\"></sup>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“I tell you,”</span> he replied, <span class=\"woj\">“if they keep quiet, the stones will cry out.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25772AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25772AE\"></sup></span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>As he approached Jerusalem and saw the city, he wept over it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25773AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25773AF\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>and said, <span class=\"woj\">“If you, even you, had only known on this day what would bring you peace—but now it is hidden from your eyes.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The days will come upon you when your enemies will build an embankment against you and encircle you and hem you in on every side.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25775AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25775AG\"></sup></span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>They will dash you to the ground, you and the children within your walls.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25776AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25776AH\"></sup> They will not leave one stone on another,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25776AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25776AI\"></sup> because you did not recognize the time of God’s coming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25776AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25776AJ\"></sup> to you.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When Jesus entered the temple courts, he began to drive out those who were selling.",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“It is written,”</span> he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“‘My house will be a house of prayer’;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25778AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25778AL\"></sup> but you have made it ‘a den of robbers.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25778AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25778AM\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Every day he was teaching at the temple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25779AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25779AN\"></sup> But the chief priests, the teachers of the law and the leaders among the people were trying to kill him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25779AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25779AO\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Yet they could not find any way to do it, because all the people hung on his words."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>One day as Jesus was teaching the people in the temple courts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25781B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25781B\"></sup> and proclaiming the good news,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25781C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25781C\"></sup> the chief priests and the teachers of the law, together with the elders, came up to him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Tell us by what authority you are doing these things,” they said. “Who gave you this authority?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25782D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25782D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“I will also ask you a question. Tell me:</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>John’s baptism<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25784E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25784E\"></sup>—was it from heaven, or of human origin?”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They discussed it among themselves and said, “If we say, ‘From heaven,’ he will ask, ‘Why didn’t you believe him?’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But if we say, ‘Of human origin,’ all the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25786F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25786F\"></sup> will stone us, because they are persuaded that John was a prophet.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25786G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25786G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they answered, “We don’t know where it was from.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Neither will I tell you by what authority I am doing these things.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He went on to tell the people this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“A man planted a vineyard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25789I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25789I\"></sup> rented it to some farmers and went away for a long time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25789J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25789J\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At harvest time he sent a servant to the tenants so they would give him some of the fruit of the vineyard. But the tenants beat him and sent him away empty-handed.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He sent another servant, but that one also they beat and treated shamefully and sent away empty-handed.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He sent still a third, and they wounded him and threw him out.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Then the owner of the vineyard said, ‘What shall I do? I will send my son, whom I love;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25793K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25793K\"></sup> perhaps they will respect him.’</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But when the tenants saw him, they talked the matter over. ‘This is the heir,’ they said. ‘Let’s kill him, and the inheritance will be ours.’</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him.</span><span class=\"woj\">“What then will the owner of the vineyard do to them?</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He will come and kill those tenants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25796L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25796L\"></sup> and give the vineyard to others.”</span>When the people heard this, they said, “God forbid!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jesus looked directly at them and asked, <span class=\"woj\">“Then what is the meaning of that which is written:</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘The stone the builders rejected</span><span class=\"woj\">has become the cornerstone’?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25797M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25797M\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces; anyone on whom it falls will be crushed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25798N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25798N\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The teachers of the law and the chief priests looked for a way to arrest him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25799O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25799O\"></sup> immediately, because they knew he had spoken this parable against them. But they were afraid of the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25799P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25799P\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Keeping a close watch on him, they sent spies, who pretended to be sincere. They hoped to catch Jesus in something he said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25800R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25800R\"></sup> so that they might hand him over to the power and authority of the governor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25800S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25800S\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the spies questioned him: “Teacher, we know that you speak and teach what is right, and that you do not show partiality but teach the way of God in accordance with the truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25801T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25801T\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Is it right for us to pay taxes to Caesar or not?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He saw through their duplicity and said to them,",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Show me a denarius. Whose image and inscription are on it?”</span>“Caesar’s,” they replied.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Then give back to Caesar what is Caesar’s,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25805U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25805U\"></sup> and to God what is God’s.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They were unable to trap him in what he had said there in public. And astonished by his answer, they became silent.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Some of the Sadducees,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25807W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25807W\"></sup> who say there is no resurrection,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25807X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25807X\"></sup> came to Jesus with a question.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Teacher,” they said, “Moses wrote for us that if a man’s brother dies and leaves a wife but no children, the man must marry the widow and raise up offspring for his brother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25808Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25808Y\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now there were seven brothers. The first one married a woman and died childless.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The second",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and then the third married her, and in the same way the seven died, leaving no children.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Finally, the woman died too.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now then, at the resurrection whose wife will she be, since the seven were married to her?”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“The people of this age marry and are given in marriage.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But those who are considered worthy of taking part in the age to come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25815Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25815Z\"></sup> and in the resurrection from the dead will neither marry nor be given in marriage,</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and they can no longer die; for they are like the angels. They are God’s children,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25816AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25816AA\"></sup> since they are children of the resurrection.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But in the account of the burning bush, even Moses showed that the dead rise, for he calls the Lord ‘the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25817AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25817AB\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He is not the God of the dead, but of the living, for to him all are alive.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Some of the teachers of the law responded, “Well said, teacher!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And no one dared to ask him any more questions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25820AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25820AC\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why is it said that the Messiah is the son of David?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25821AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25821AE\"></sup></span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>David himself declares in the Book of Psalms:</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘The Lord said to my Lord:</span><span class=\"woj\">“Sit at my right hand</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>until I make your enemies</span><span class=\"woj\">a footstool for your feet.”’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25823AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25823AF\"></sup></span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>David calls him ‘Lord.’ How then can he be his son?”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>While all the people were listening, Jesus said to his disciples,",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Beware of the teachers of the law. They like to walk around in flowing robes and love to be greeted with respect in the marketplaces and have the most important seats in the synagogues and the places of honor at banquets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25826AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25826AG\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>They devour widows’ houses and for a show make lengthy prayers. These men will be punished most severely.”</span>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>As Jesus looked up, he saw the rich putting their gifts into the temple treasury.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25828B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25828B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He also saw a poor widow put in two very small copper coins.",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Truly I tell you,”</span> he said, <span class=\"woj\">“this poor widow has put in more than all the others.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>All these people gave their gifts out of their wealth; but she out of her poverty put in all she had to live on.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25831C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25831C\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Some of his disciples were remarking about how the temple was adorned with beautiful stones and with gifts dedicated to God. But Jesus said,",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“As for what you see here, the time will come when not one stone will be left on another;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25833F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25833F\"></sup> every one of them will be thrown down.”</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Teacher,” they asked, “when will these things happen? And what will be the sign that they are about to take place?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He replied: <span class=\"woj\">“Watch out that you are not deceived. For many will come in my name, claiming, ‘I am he,’ and, ‘The time is near.’ Do not follow them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25835G\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When you hear of wars and uprisings, do not be frightened. These things must happen first, but the end will not come right away.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he said to them: <span class=\"woj\">“Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25837H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25837H\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There will be great earthquakes, famines and pestilences in various places, and fearful events and great signs from heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25838I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25838I\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“But before all this, they will seize you and persecute you. They will hand you over to synagogues and put you in prison, and you will be brought before kings and governors, and all on account of my name.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And so you will bear testimony to me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25840J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25840J\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But make up your mind not to worry beforehand how you will defend yourselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25841K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25841K\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For I will give you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25842L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25842L\"></sup> words and wisdom that none of your adversaries will be able to resist or contradict.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You will be betrayed even by parents, brothers and sisters, relatives and friends,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25843M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25843M\"></sup> and they will put some of you to death.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Everyone will hate you because of me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25844N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25844N\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But not a hair of your head will perish.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25845O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25845O\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Stand firm, and you will win life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25846P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25846P\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When you see Jerusalem being surrounded by armies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25847Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25847Q\"></sup> you will know that its desolation is near.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains, let those in the city get out, and let those in the country not enter the city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25848R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25848R\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For this is the time of punishment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25849S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25849S\"></sup> in fulfillment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25849T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25849T\"></sup> of all that has been written.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>How dreadful it will be in those days for pregnant women and nursing mothers! There will be great distress in the land and wrath against this people.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They will fall by the sword and will be taken as prisoners to all the nations. Jerusalem will be trampled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25851U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25851U\"></sup> on by the Gentiles until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“There will be signs in the sun, moon and stars. On the earth, nations will be in anguish and perplexity at the roaring and tossing of the sea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25852V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25852V\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>People will faint from terror, apprehensive of what is coming on the world, for the heavenly bodies will be shaken.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25853W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25853W\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>At that time they will see the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25854X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25854X\"></sup> coming in a cloud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25854Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25854Y\"></sup> with power and great glory.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When these things begin to take place, stand up and lift up your heads, because your redemption is drawing near.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25855Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25855Z\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He told them this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“Look at the fig tree and all the trees.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When they sprout leaves, you can see for yourselves and know that summer is near.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Even so, when you see these things happening, you know that the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25858AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25858AA\"></sup> is near.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Truly I tell you, this generation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25859AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25859AB\"></sup> will certainly not pass away until all these things have happened.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will never pass away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25860AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25860AC\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Be careful, or your hearts will be weighed down with carousing, drunkenness and the anxieties of life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25861AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25861AD\"></sup> and that day will close on you suddenly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25861AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25861AE\"></sup> like a trap.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>For it will come on all those who live on the face of the whole earth.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Be always on the watch, and pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25863AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25863AF\"></sup> that you may be able to escape all that is about to happen, and that you may be able to stand before the Son of Man.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Each day Jesus was teaching at the temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25864AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25864AG\"></sup> and each evening he went out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25864AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25864AH\"></sup> to spend the night on the hill called the Mount of Olives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25864AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25864AI\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and all the people came early in the morning to hear him at the temple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25865AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25865AJ\"></sup>"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Now the Festival of Unleavened Bread, called the Passover, was approaching,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25866B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25866B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and the chief priests and the teachers of the law were looking for some way to get rid of Jesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25867C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25867C\"></sup> for they were afraid of the people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Satan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25868D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25868D\"></sup> entered Judas, called Iscariot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25868E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25868E\"></sup> one of the Twelve.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Judas went to the chief priests and the officers of the temple guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25869F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25869F\"></sup> and discussed with them how he might betray Jesus.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They were delighted and agreed to give him money.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25870G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25870G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He consented, and watched for an opportunity to hand Jesus over to them when no crowd was present.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then came the day of Unleavened Bread on which the Passover lamb had to be sacrificed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25872M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25872M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jesus sent Peter and John,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25873N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25873N\"></sup> saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Go and make preparations for us to eat the Passover.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Where do you want us to prepare for it?” they asked.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“As you enter the city, a man carrying a jar of water will meet you. Follow him to the house that he enters,</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and say to the owner of the house, ‘The Teacher asks: Where is the guest room, where I may eat the Passover with my disciples?’</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He will show you a large room upstairs, all furnished. Make preparations there.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They left and found things just as Jesus had told them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25878O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25878O\"></sup> So they prepared the Passover.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When the hour came, Jesus and his apostles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25879P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25879P\"></sup> reclined at the table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25879Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25879Q\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I have eagerly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25880R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25880R\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For I tell you, I will not eat it again until it finds fulfillment in the kingdom of God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25881S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25881S\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After taking the cup, he gave thanks and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Take this and divide it among you.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For I tell you I will not drink again from the fruit of the vine until the kingdom of God comes.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he took bread, gave thanks and broke it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25884T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25884T\"></sup> and gave it to them, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“This is my body given for you; do this in remembrance of me.”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In the same way, after the supper he took the cup, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“This cup is the new covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25885U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25885U\"></sup> in my blood, which is poured out for you.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But the hand of him who is going to betray me is with mine on the table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25886V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25886V\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25887W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25887W\"></sup> will go as it has been decreed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25887X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25887X\"></sup> But woe to that man who betrays him!”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They began to question among themselves which of them it might be who would do this.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>A dispute also arose among them as to which of them was considered to be greatest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25889Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25889Y\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“The kings of the Gentiles lord it over them; and those who exercise authority over them call themselves Benefactors.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But you are not to be like that. Instead, the greatest among you should be like the youngest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25891Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25891Z\"></sup> and the one who rules like the one who serves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25891AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25891AA\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For who is greater, the one who is at the table or the one who serves? Is it not the one who is at the table? But I am among you as one who serves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25892AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25892AB\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You are those who have stood by me in my trials.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And I confer on you a kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25894AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25894AC\"></sup> just as my Father conferred one on me,</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>so that you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25895AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25895AD\"></sup> and sit on thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25895AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25895AE\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Simon, Simon, Satan has asked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25896AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25896AF\"></sup> to sift all of you as wheat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25896AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25896AG\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But I have prayed for you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25897AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25897AH\"></sup> Simon, that your faith may not fail. And when you have turned back, strengthen your brothers.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25897AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25897AI\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But he replied, “Lord, I am ready to go with you to prison and to death.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25898AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25898AJ\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“I tell you, Peter, before the rooster crows today, you will deny three times that you know me.”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then Jesus asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“When I sent you without purse, bag or sandals,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25900AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25900AK\"></sup> did you lack anything?”</span>“Nothing,” they answered.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“But now if you have a purse, take it, and also a bag; and if you don’t have a sword, sell your cloak and buy one.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>It is written: ‘And he was numbered with the transgressors’;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25902AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25902AL\"></sup> and I tell you that this must be fulfilled in me. Yes, what is written about me is reaching its fulfillment.”</span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The disciples said, “See, Lord, here are two swords.”<span class=\"woj\">“That’s enough!”</span> he replied.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Jesus went out as usual<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25904AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25904AN\"></sup> to the Mount of Olives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25904AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25904AO\"></sup> and his disciples followed him.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>On reaching the place, he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Pray that you will not fall into temptation.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25905AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25905AP\"></sup></span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He withdrew about a stone’s throw beyond them, knelt down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25906AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25906AQ\"></sup> and prayed,",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“Father, if you are willing, take this cup<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25907AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25907AR\"></sup> from me; yet not my will, but yours be done.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25907AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25907AS\"></sup></span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>An angel from heaven appeared to him and strengthened him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25908AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25908AT\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>And being in anguish, he prayed more earnestly, and his sweat was like drops of blood falling to the ground.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When he rose from prayer and went back to the disciples, he found them asleep, exhausted from sorrow.",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Why are you sleeping?”</span> he asked them. <span class=\"woj\">“Get up and pray so that you will not fall into temptation.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25911AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25911AU\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>While he was still speaking a crowd came up, and the man who was called Judas, one of the Twelve, was leading them. He approached Jesus to kiss him,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>but Jesus asked him, <span class=\"woj\">“Judas, are you betraying the Son of Man with a kiss?”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>When Jesus’ followers saw what was going to happen, they said, “Lord, should we strike with our swords?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25914AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25914AW\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And one of them struck the servant of the high priest, cutting off his right ear.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>But Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“No more of this!”</span> And he touched the man’s ear and healed him.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Then Jesus said to the chief priests, the officers of the temple guard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25917AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25917AX\"></sup> and the elders, who had come for him, <span class=\"woj\">“Am I leading a rebellion, that you have come with swords and clubs?</span>",
			"53": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Every day I was with you in the temple courts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25918AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25918AY\"></sup> and you did not lay a hand on me. But this is your hour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25918AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25918AZ\"></sup>—when darkness reigns.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25918BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25918BA\"></sup></span>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Then seizing him, they led him away and took him into the house of the high priest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25919BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25919BC\"></sup> Peter followed at a distance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25919BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25919BD\"></sup>",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And when some there had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard and had sat down together, Peter sat down with them.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>A servant girl saw him seated there in the firelight. She looked closely at him and said, “This man was with him.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>But he denied it. “Woman, I don’t know him,” he said.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>A little later someone else saw him and said, “You also are one of them.”“Man, I am not!” Peter replied.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>About an hour later another asserted, “Certainly this fellow was with him, for he is a Galilean.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25924BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25924BE\"></sup>",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>Peter replied, “Man, I don’t know what you’re talking about!” Just as he was speaking, the rooster crowed.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>The Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25926BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25926BF\"></sup> turned and looked straight at Peter. Then Peter remembered the word the Lord had spoken to him: <span class=\"woj\">“Before the rooster crows today, you will disown me three times.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25926BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25926BG\"></sup></span>",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>And he went outside and wept bitterly.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>The men who were guarding Jesus began mocking and beating him.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>They blindfolded him and demanded, “Prophesy! Who hit you?”",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>And they said many other insulting things to him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25930BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25930BI\"></sup>",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>At daybreak the council<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25931BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25931BM\"></sup> of the elders of the people, both the chief priests and the teachers of the law, met together,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25931BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25931BN\"></sup> and Jesus was led before them.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>“If you are the Messiah,” they said, “tell us.”Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“If I tell you, you will not believe me,</span>",
			"68": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>and if I asked you, you would not answer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25933BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25933BO\"></sup></span>",
			"69": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>But from now on, the Son of Man will be seated at the right hand of the mighty God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25934BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25934BP\"></sup></span>",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>They all asked, “Are you then the Son of God?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25935BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25935BQ\"></sup>He replied, <span class=\"woj\">“You say that I am.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25935BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25935BR\"></sup></span>",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>Then they said, “Why do we need any more testimony? We have heard it from his own lips.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Then the whole assembly rose and led him off to Pilate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25937A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25937A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they began to accuse him, saying, “We have found this man subverting our nation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25938B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25938B\"></sup> He opposes payment of taxes to Caesar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25938C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25938C\"></sup> and claims to be Messiah, a king.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25938D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25938D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Pilate asked Jesus, “Are you the king of the Jews?”<span class=\"woj\">“You have said so,”</span> Jesus replied.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Pilate announced to the chief priests and the crowd, “I find no basis for a charge against this man.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25940E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25940E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But they insisted, “He stirs up the people all over Judea by his teaching. He started in Galilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25941F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25941F\"></sup> and has come all the way here.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>On hearing this, Pilate asked if the man was a Galilean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25942G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25942G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he learned that Jesus was under Herod’s jurisdiction, he sent him to Herod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25943H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25943H\"></sup> who was also in Jerusalem at that time.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Herod saw Jesus, he was greatly pleased, because for a long time he had been wanting to see him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25944I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25944I\"></sup> From what he had heard about him, he hoped to see him perform a sign of some sort.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He plied him with many questions, but Jesus gave him no answer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25945J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25945J\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The chief priests and the teachers of the law were standing there, vehemently accusing him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Herod and his soldiers ridiculed and mocked him. Dressing him in an elegant robe,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25947K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25947K\"></sup> they sent him back to Pilate.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>That day Herod and Pilate became friends<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25948L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25948L\"></sup>—before this they had been enemies.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Pilate called together the chief priests, the rulers and the people,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and said to them, “You brought me this man as one who was inciting the people to rebellion. I have examined him in your presence and have found no basis for your charges against him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25950M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25950M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Neither has Herod, for he sent him back to us; as you can see, he has done nothing to deserve death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Therefore, I will punish him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25952N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25952N\"></sup> and then release him.”<sup class=\"versenum\">[17] </sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the whole crowd shouted, “Away with this man! Release Barabbas to us!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25954O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25954O\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>(Barabbas had been thrown into prison for an insurrection in the city, and for murder.)",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Wanting to release Jesus, Pilate appealed to them again.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But they kept shouting, “Crucify him! Crucify him!”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For the third time he spoke to them: “Why? What crime has this man committed? I have found in him no grounds for the death penalty. Therefore I will have him punished and then release him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25958P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25958P\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But with loud shouts they insistently demanded that he be crucified, and their shouts prevailed.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Pilate decided to grant their demand.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He released the man who had been thrown into prison for insurrection and murder, the one they asked for, and surrendered Jesus to their will.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>As the soldiers led him away, they seized Simon from Cyrene,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25962R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25962R\"></sup> who was on his way in from the country, and put the cross on him and made him carry it behind Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25962S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25962S\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>A large number of people followed him, including women who mourned and wailed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25963T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25963T\"></sup> for him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jesus turned and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me; weep for yourselves and for your children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25964U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25964U\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For the time will come when you will say, ‘Blessed are the childless women, the wombs that never bore and the breasts that never nursed!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25965V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25965V\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then</span><span class=\"woj\">“‘they will say to the mountains, “Fall on us!”</span><span class=\"woj\">and to the hills, “Cover us!”’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25966W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25966W\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For if people do these things when the tree is green, what will happen when it is dry?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25967X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25967X\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Two other men, both criminals, were also led out with him to be executed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25968Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25968Y\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When they came to the place called the Skull, they crucified him there, along with the criminals—one on his right, the other on his left.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25970Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25970Z\"></sup> forgive them, for they do not know what they are doing.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25970AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25970AA\"></sup></span> And they divided up his clothes by casting lots.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25970AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25970AB\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The people stood watching, and the rulers even sneered at him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25971AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25971AC\"></sup> They said, “He saved others; let him save himself if he is God’s Messiah, the Chosen One.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25971AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25971AD\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The soldiers also came up and mocked him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25972AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25972AE\"></sup> They offered him wine vinegar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25972AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25972AF\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and said, “If you are the king of the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25973AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25973AG\"></sup> save yourself.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>There was a written notice above him, which read: <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">this is the king of the jews</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25974AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25974AH\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>One of the criminals who hung there hurled insults at him: “Aren’t you the Messiah? Save yourself and us!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25975AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25975AI\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But the other criminal rebuked him. “Don’t you fear God,” he said, “since you are under the same sentence?",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>We are punished justly, for we are getting what our deeds deserve. But this man has done nothing wrong.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25977AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25977AJ\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then he said, “Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25978AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25978AK\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Jesus answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I tell you, today you will be with me in paradise.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25979AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25979AL\"></sup></span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>It was now about noon, and darkness came over the whole land until three in the afternoon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25980AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25980AN\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>for the sun stopped shining. And the curtain of the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25981AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25981AO\"></sup> was torn in two.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25981AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25981AP\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Jesus called out with a loud voice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25982AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25982AQ\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">“Father, into your hands I commit my spirit.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25982AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25982AR\"></sup></span> When he had said this, he breathed his last.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25982AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25982AS\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>The centurion, seeing what had happened, praised God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25983AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25983AT\"></sup> and said, “Surely this was a righteous man.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>When all the people who had gathered to witness this sight saw what took place, they beat their breasts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25984AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25984AU\"></sup> and went away.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But all those who knew him, including the women who had followed him from Galilee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25985AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25985AV\"></sup> stood at a distance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25985AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25985AW\"></sup> watching these things.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Now there was a man named Joseph, a member of the Council, a good and upright man,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>who had not consented to their decision and action. He came from the Judean town of Arimathea, and he himself was waiting for the kingdom of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25987AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25987AY\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Going to Pilate, he asked for Jesus’ body.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Then he took it down, wrapped it in linen cloth and placed it in a tomb cut in the rock, one in which no one had yet been laid.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>It was Preparation Day,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25990AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25990AZ\"></sup> and the Sabbath was about to begin.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>The women who had come with Jesus from Galilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25991BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25991BA\"></sup> followed Joseph and saw the tomb and how his body was laid in it.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Then they went home and prepared spices and perfumes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25992BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25992BB\"></sup> But they rested on the Sabbath in obedience to the commandment.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25992BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25992BC\"></sup>"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>On the first day of the week, very early in the morning, the women took the spices they had prepared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25993B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25993B\"></sup> and went to the tomb.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They found the stone rolled away from the tomb,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but when they entered, they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25995C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25995C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>While they were wondering about this, suddenly two men in clothes that gleamed like lightning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25996D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25996D\"></sup> stood beside them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In their fright the women bowed down with their faces to the ground, but the men said to them, “Why do you look for the living among the dead?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He is not here; he has risen! Remember how he told you, while he was still with you in Galilee:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25998E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25998E\"></sup>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘The Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25999F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25999F\"></sup> must be delivered over to the hands of sinners, be crucified and on the third day be raised again.’</span> ”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25999G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25999G\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they remembered his words.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26000H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26000H\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they came back from the tomb, they told all these things to the Eleven and to all the others.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It was Mary Magdalene, Joanna, Mary the mother of James, and the others with them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26002I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26002I\"></sup> who told this to the apostles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26002J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26002J\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But they did not believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26003K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26003K\"></sup> the women, because their words seemed to them like nonsense.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Peter, however, got up and ran to the tomb. Bending over, he saw the strips of linen lying by themselves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26004L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26004L\"></sup> and he went away,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26004M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26004M\"></sup> wondering to himself what had happened.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now that same day two of them were going to a village called Emmaus, about seven miles from Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26005N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26005N\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They were talking with each other about everything that had happened.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As they talked and discussed these things with each other, Jesus himself came up and walked along with them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26007O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26007O\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>but they were kept from recognizing him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26008P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26008P\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“What are you discussing together as you walk along?”</span>They stood still, their faces downcast.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>One of them, named Cleopas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26010Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26010Q\"></sup> asked him, “Are you the only one visiting Jerusalem who does not know the things that have happened there in these days?”",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“What things?”</span> he asked.“About Jesus of Nazareth,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26011R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26011R\"></sup> they replied. “He was a prophet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26011S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26011S\"></sup> powerful in word and deed before God and all the people.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The chief priests and our rulers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26012T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26012T\"></sup> handed him over to be sentenced to death, and they crucified him;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but we had hoped that he was the one who was going to redeem Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26013U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26013U\"></sup> And what is more, it is the third day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26013V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26013V\"></sup> since all this took place.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In addition, some of our women amazed us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26014W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26014W\"></sup> They went to the tomb early this morning",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>but didn’t find his body. They came and told us that they had seen a vision of angels, who said he was alive.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then some of our companions went to the tomb and found it just as the women had said, but they did not see Jesus.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26016X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26016X\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“How foolish you are, and how slow to believe all that the prophets have spoken!</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Did not the Messiah have to suffer these things and then enter his glory?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26018Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26018Y\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And beginning with Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26019Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26019Z\"></sup> and all the Prophets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26019AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26019AA\"></sup> he explained to them what was said in all the Scriptures concerning himself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26019AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26019AB\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>As they approached the village to which they were going, Jesus continued on as if he were going farther.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But they urged him strongly, “Stay with us, for it is nearly evening; the day is almost over.” So he went in to stay with them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When he was at the table with them, he took bread, gave thanks, broke it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26022AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26022AC\"></sup> and began to give it to them.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then their eyes were opened and they recognized him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26023AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26023AD\"></sup> and he disappeared from their sight.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They asked each other, “Were not our hearts burning within us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26024AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26024AE\"></sup> while he talked with us on the road and opened the Scriptures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26024AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26024AF\"></sup> to us?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They got up and returned at once to Jerusalem. There they found the Eleven and those with them, assembled together",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and saying, “It is true! The Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26026AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26026AG\"></sup> has risen and has appeared to Simon.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26026AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26026AH\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then the two told what had happened on the way, and how Jesus was recognized by them when he broke the bread.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26027AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26027AI\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>While they were still talking about this, Jesus himself stood among them and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Peace be with you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26028AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26028AJ\"></sup></span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They were startled and frightened, thinking they saw a ghost.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26029AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26029AK\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you troubled, and why do doubts rise in your minds?</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Look at my hands and my feet. It is I myself! Touch me and see;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26031AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26031AL\"></sup> a ghost does not have flesh and bones, as you see I have.”</span>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>When he had said this, he showed them his hands and feet.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And while they still did not believe it because of joy and amazement, he asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you have anything here to eat?”</span>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They gave him a piece of broiled fish,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and he took it and ate it in their presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26035AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26035AM\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“This is what I told you while I was still with you:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26036AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26036AN\"></sup> Everything must be fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26036AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26036AO\"></sup> that is written about me in the Law of Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26036AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26036AP\"></sup> the Prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26036AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26036AQ\"></sup> and the Psalms.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26036AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26036AR\"></sup></span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then he opened their minds so they could understand the Scriptures.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He told them, <span class=\"woj\">“This is what is written: The Messiah will suffer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26038AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26038AS\"></sup> and rise from the dead on the third day,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26038AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26038AT\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>and repentance for the forgiveness of sins will be preached in his name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26039AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26039AU\"></sup> to all nations,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26039AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26039AV\"></sup> beginning at Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26039AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26039AW\"></sup></span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>You are witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26040AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26040AX\"></sup> of these things.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>I am going to send you what my Father has promised;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26041AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26041AY\"></sup> but stay in the city until you have been clothed with power from on high.”</span>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>When he had led them out to the vicinity of Bethany,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26042AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26042AZ\"></sup> he lifted up his hands and blessed them.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>While he was blessing them, he left them and was taken up into heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26043BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26043BA\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Then they worshiped him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And they stayed continually at the temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26045BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26045BB\"></sup> praising God."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;